2
00:00:24.582 --> 00:00:26.584
[faint beeping]

3
00:00:26.649 --> 00:00:30.287
[deep breathing]

4
00:00:33.357 --> 00:00:35.359
[ethereal music playing]

5
00:01:08.077 --> 00:01:10.358
Subtitles retimed/edited by Cuvio.
Missing lines restored.

6
00:01:11.462 --> 00:01:13.897
[Mary] <i>Eye movement detected.</i>

7
00:01:14.532 --> 00:01:16.900
[zipper creaking]

8
00:01:17.401 --> 00:01:19.336
[whirring]

9
00:01:21.372 --> 00:01:22.672
[choking]

10
00:01:24.308 --> 00:01:26.075
[coughing. gagging]

11
00:01:27.344 --> 00:01:28.379
[groans]

12
00:01:28.978 --> 00:01:31.215
[Mary] <i>What is two plus two?</i>

13
00:01:31.282 --> 00:01:32.316
[coughing]

14
00:01:32.849 --> 00:01:34.618
[Mary] <i>Incorrect.</i>

15
00:01:35.152 --> 00:01:37.588
<i>Cognition assessment</i> -[coughs]

16
00:01:37.655 --> 00:01:39.789
- [Mary] <i>What is two plus two?</i>
- [teeth clacking]

17
00:01:39.856 --> 00:01:41.325
<i>- Incorrect.</i>
- [grunts]

18
00:01:41.858 --> 00:01:44.528
<i>You have been in an induced coma.</i>

19
00:01:44.595 --> 00:01:46.095
[breathes deeply]

20
00:01:46.163 --> 00:01:47.806
- [hair trimmer whirring]
<i>- You may experience</i>

21
00:01:47.830 --> 00:01:49.400
<i>some memory loss</i> -[spits]

22
00:01:49.466 --> 00:01:50.467
<i>difficulty speaking.</i>

23
00:01:50.534 --> 00:01:52.203
[yelps]

24
00:01:53.069 --> 00:01:54.471
- [thudding]
- [groans]

25
00:01:54.605 --> 00:01:56.307
[Mary] <i>Body movement detected.</i>

26
00:01:56.839 --> 00:01:58.309
<i>For your own safety.</i>

27
00:01:58.375 --> 00:02:00.678
<i>please return to the medical platform.</i>

28
00:02:00.743 --> 00:02:02.045
[groaning]

29
00:02:08.552 --> 00:02:09.919
Where am I?

30
00:02:09.986 --> 00:02:11.721
[Mary]
<i>Please remember muscle function</i>

31
00:02:11.788 --> 00:02:13.957
<i>has not yet been restored.</i>

32
00:02:16.826 --> 00:02:18.861
- [whirring]
- [objects clattering]

33
00:02:29.221 --> 00:02:30.524
[man] People!

34
00:02:31.123 --> 00:02:32.559
Hello?

35
00:02:37.698 --> 00:02:39.533
[music fades]

36
00:02:42.836 --> 00:02:44.270
[breathing deeply]

37
00:02:45.872 --> 00:02:47.173
[grunts]

38
00:02:50.409 --> 00:02:51.812
- [thudding]
- [grunting]

39
00:02:56.382 --> 00:02:58.485
[intriguing music playing]

40
00:03:02.723 --> 00:03:03.824
[grunts]

41
00:03:04.591 --> 00:03:05.692
[panting]

42
00:03:17.657 --> 00:03:19.426
Where am I?

43
00:03:44.498 --> 00:03:46.500
[breath trembling]

44
00:03:54.775 --> 00:03:55.909
[music fades]

45
00:04:00.273 --> 00:04:01.841
Red leather. yellow leather.

46
00:04:02.181 --> 00:04:03.817
[blabbers]

47
00:04:06.920 --> 00:04:08.589
Why is there an atomic resolution

48
00:04:08.656 --> 00:04:10.391
scanning electron microscope?

49
00:04:11.058 --> 00:04:12.359
Why do I know that?

50
00:04:13.527 --> 00:04:15.029
Am I smart?

51
00:04:17.431 --> 00:04:19.400
[soft intriguing music playing]

52
00:04:24.405 --> 00:04:25.705
[birds chirping]

53
00:04:51.148 --> 00:04:52.349
Hello?

54
00:04:53.083 --> 00:04:54.418
[Mary] <i>Please record video diary.</i>

55
00:04:54.485 --> 00:04:55.785
[man] No.

56
00:04:55.852 --> 00:04:58.755
Can I speak to the person in charge?

57
00:04:58.821 --> 00:04:59.924
[blabbers]

58
00:04:59.990 --> 00:05:01.358
The. uh. captain.

59
00:05:01.425 --> 00:05:03.961
[Mary] <i>Captain Yáo. Li-Jie. Deceased.</i>

60
00:05:04.028 --> 00:05:07.298
Yeah. where. um. are the living people?

61
00:05:08.332 --> 00:05:10.334
- [grunts]
- [Mary] <i>Dr. Ryland Grace.</i>

62
00:05:10.800 --> 00:05:12.336
<i>End of manifest.</i>

63
00:05:15.172 --> 00:05:19.910
I can't be the only person here. Right?

64
00:05:19.977 --> 00:05:21.645
[Mary] <i>Pilot detected.</i>

65
00:05:21.711 --> 00:05:23.722
- [systems powering up]
- No! No. No-No. Not the pilot.

66
00:05:23.746 --> 00:05:25.349
Uh.

67
00:05:25.416 --> 00:05:27.618
Call. uh. Houston.

68
00:05:27.685 --> 00:05:28.818
[Mary] <i>Unknown command.</i>

69
00:05:28.885 --> 00:05:31.721
Operation Go Home in effect.

70
00:05:31.788 --> 00:05:33.357
[Mary] <i>Invalid operation.</i>

71
00:05:33.424 --> 00:05:34.791
[trackball clicking]

72
00:05:34.857 --> 00:05:37.494
That's the sun! There it is.

73
00:05:37.928 --> 00:05:40.431
So. what are we. like. Neptune-ish?

74
00:05:41.966 --> 00:05:44.867
Let's crank up the radio and call Earth.

75
00:05:44.935 --> 00:05:47.004
[Mary] <i>Current</i>
<i>transmission time to Earth</i>

76
00:05:47.071 --> 00:05:51.976
<i>is 11 years. 10 months.
14 days and 6 hours.</i>

77
00:05:52.042 --> 00:05:54.811
No. Nope. You're wrong.

78
00:05:54.877 --> 00:05:56.480
I need a map.

79
00:05:58.415 --> 00:05:59.782
Oh.

80
00:06:00.150 --> 00:06:00.918
Uh.

81
00:06:00.985 --> 00:06:02.819
That's so far.

82
00:06:02.885 --> 00:06:06.023
That's really far. Uh

83
00:06:06.523 --> 00:06:08.825
[trackball continues spinning]

84
00:06:14.831 --> 00:06:16.166
[sighs]

85
00:06:16.233 --> 00:06:18.302
[softly] That's not our sun.

86
00:06:21.804 --> 00:06:23.741
[in normal voice] That's not our sun.

87
00:06:23.806 --> 00:06:25.476
[intriguing electronic music playing]

88
00:06:33.450 --> 00:06:35.152
[thudding]

89
00:06:37.421 --> 00:06:39.189
Where is the fuel?

90
00:06:45.396 --> 00:06:46.497
Wait.

91
00:06:58.976 --> 00:07:00.044
[music fades]

92
00:07:00.110 --> 00:07:01.912
[uneasy music playing]

93
00:07:15.292 --> 00:07:16.927
[inaudible]

94
00:07:18.828 --> 00:07:20.497
[riveting music playing]

95
00:07:20.631 --> 00:07:23.067
[reporter] <i>We are just</i>
<i>minutes away from the fly-by</i>

96
00:07:23.133 --> 00:07:25.202
<i>through the Petrova line near Venus.</i>

97
00:07:25.269 --> 00:07:28.272
<i>So. what can you tell us
about the ArcLight probe?</i>

98
00:07:28.739 --> 00:07:31.342
<i>What do we expect to find?</i>

99
00:07:32.743 --> 00:07:34.311
[Dr. Browne] <i>The image we see</i>

100
00:07:34.378 --> 00:07:36.098
<i>will be coming
from the on board microscope.</i>

101
00:07:39.553 --> 00:07:41.952
Um Oh. my God.

102
00:07:46.568 --> 00:07:49.004
<i>Sorry. I have to go now.</i>

103
00:07:55.699 --> 00:07:57.368
[humming]

104
00:07:57.434 --> 00:08:03.040
[in sing-song voice]
Sound waves are physical.

105
00:08:03.107 --> 00:08:07.344
And at different frequencies.

106
00:08:07.411 --> 00:08:10.581
they make different
[high-pitched] pattern...

107
00:08:10.647 --> 00:08:12.082
No. pattern...

108
00:08:12.149 --> 00:08:13.593
They make different [low-pitched] patt...

109
00:08:13.617 --> 00:08:15.586
Olivia. can you
help me out? There we go!

110
00:08:15.652 --> 00:08:17.421
[beat droning]

111
00:08:17.488 --> 00:08:18.589
Whoa!

112
00:08:19.149 --> 00:08:20.050
Yeah.

113
00:08:20.141 --> 00:08:22.176
Are they really eating the sun?

114
00:08:22.243 --> 00:08:24.078
The space dots?

115
00:08:24.145 --> 00:08:26.180
That is a great question. uh. Rekha.

116
00:08:26.247 --> 00:08:29.583
And I'd be curious what
your parents think about that.

117
00:08:29.649 --> 00:08:31.619
I'm not sure it should come from me.

118
00:08:31.685 --> 00:08:34.255
Hey! Who wants to play a game of

119
00:08:34.321 --> 00:08:36.423
the bean bag is lava!

120
00:08:36.490 --> 00:08:39.059
[students] Lava! Lava! Lava!

121
00:08:39.126 --> 00:08:41.629
What is the speed of light. Olivia?

122
00:08:41.695 --> 00:08:42.997
Uh.

123
00:08:43.063 --> 00:08:44.343
It's melting your hands. Olivia!

124
00:08:44.398 --> 00:08:46.767
186.000 miles per second!

125
00:08:46.834 --> 00:08:48.802
Oh! Give her a round of applause.

126
00:08:48.869 --> 00:08:50.971
That is awesome.

127
00:08:51.329 --> 00:08:53.474
What is the Petrova line?

128
00:08:54.392 --> 00:08:55.476
[chuckles sheepishly] Pass!

129
00:08:55.543 --> 00:08:56.810
You can't pass!

130
00:08:57.056 --> 00:08:58.012
I just did.

131
00:08:58.078 --> 00:09:00.381
[students] Lava! Lava! Lava!

132
00:09:00.447 --> 00:09:01.849
Come on. guys.

133
00:09:01.916 --> 00:09:03.551
Two years ago

134
00:09:04.451 --> 00:09:08.622
a radio telescope enthusiast
named Irina Petrova.

135
00:09:09.290 --> 00:09:10.925
she noticed that there was a streak

136
00:09:10.991 --> 00:09:14.161
of infrared light from the sun to Venus.

137
00:09:14.528 --> 00:09:17.364
And that is now known
as the Petrova line.

138
00:09:17.431 --> 00:09:18.432
That's it.

139
00:09:18.499 --> 00:09:19.833
That's the dots?

140
00:09:20.142 --> 00:09:21.142
They think so.

141
00:09:21.168 --> 00:09:22.803
What dots?

142
00:09:26.137 --> 00:09:28.042
[Grace] These dots.

143
00:09:28.108 --> 00:09:30.411
They sent a probe up to the Petrova line.

144
00:09:30.477 --> 00:09:32.713
and this is what they found.

145
00:09:33.682 --> 00:09:35.749
Are they eating the sun?

146
00:09:37.418 --> 00:09:38.919
They seem to be

147
00:09:38.986 --> 00:09:43.557
dimming the sun a tiny.
teeny-weeny. little bit.

148
00:09:44.058 --> 00:09:45.459
So. no big whoop.

149
00:09:45.526 --> 00:09:46.760
It's a small whoop.

150
00:09:47.356 --> 00:09:48.824
It's a small-to-medium whoop.

151
00:09:49.330 --> 00:09:52.866
Over the next 30 years. the Earth could

152
00:09:52.933 --> 00:09:55.970
cool maybe 10

153
00:09:56.705 --> 00:09:58.305
to 15 degrees.

154
00:09:58.839 --> 00:10:00.808
So it <i>is</i> a big whoop.

155
00:10:00.874 --> 00:10:03.143
I heard that all the crops will die.

156
00:10:03.210 --> 00:10:04.878
the economy will free-fall.

157
00:10:04.945 --> 00:10:06.625
and half the Earth will die of starvation.

158
00:10:07.496 --> 00:10:08.315
- [overlapping chatter]
- Well.

159
00:10:08.382 --> 00:10:09.850
We're all gonna die!

160
00:10:09.917 --> 00:10:11.218
Yeah. it's true.

161
00:10:11.285 --> 00:10:13.120
[Grace] You're forgetting something.

162
00:10:13.187 --> 00:10:15.889
Guys. guys! That's <i>if</i>
that were to happen. Right?

163
00:10:15.956 --> 00:10:18.058
They're gonna figure this out.

164
00:10:18.125 --> 00:10:23.564
Right now. the best minds
in the entire world are on it.

165
00:10:23.631 --> 00:10:25.266
[music ends abruptly]

166
00:10:28.369 --> 00:10:30.004
[hair trimmer whirring]

167
00:10:32.239 --> 00:10:35.042
- [country song playing]
- [whirring]

168
00:10:38.169 --> 00:10:46.142
Well. I woke up Sunday morning with no
way to hold my head that didn't hurt...

169
00:10:48.757 --> 00:10:51.025
[Mary] <i>Good morning. Dr. Grace.</i>

170
00:10:51.992 --> 00:10:53.827
[Grace] I'm up!

171
00:10:58.700 --> 00:11:00.334
[crunching]

172
00:11:02.451 --> 00:11:10.251
Then I headed back for home and somewhere
far away a lonely bell was ringing.

173
00:11:10.311 --> 00:11:12.279
[inaudible]

174
00:11:14.576 --> 00:11:22.576
And it echoed through the canyons like
the disappearing dreams of yesterday.

175
00:11:24.701 --> 00:11:32.701
On the Sunday Morning
sidewalk wishing Lord I was stoned.

176
00:11:36.728 --> 00:11:44.728
Cause there's something in a
Sunday makes a body feel alone.

177
00:11:48.622 --> 00:11:56.622
And there's nothing short of
dying half as lonesome as the sound.

178
00:12:00.358 --> 00:12:08.358
On the sleeping city sidewalk
Sunday morning coming down.

179
00:12:32.359 --> 00:12:34.027
- [door rattles]
- [woman] Knock. knock.

180
00:12:34.094 --> 00:12:35.396
[song ends]

181
00:12:35.929 --> 00:12:36.930
Who's there?

182
00:12:36.997 --> 00:12:38.298
Not good at jokes.

183
00:12:38.365 --> 00:12:40.134
[Grace] Not good
at jokes who? [Chuckles]

184
00:12:43.705 --> 00:12:45.372
Dr. Grace?

185
00:12:46.974 --> 00:12:48.475
Maybe.

186
00:12:48.542 --> 00:12:49.953
Eva Stratt. I'm with
the Petrova Task Force.

187
00:12:49.977 --> 00:12:51.278
I need your help.

188
00:12:51.864 --> 00:12:52.613
Me.

189
00:12:52.680 --> 00:12:54.281
Did you write this?

190
00:12:57.223 --> 00:12:58.252
Oh.

191
00:12:58.318 --> 00:12:59.854
I'm interested in this section here.

192
00:12:59.920 --> 00:13:01.455
Uh -Page 31.

193
00:13:01.522 --> 00:13:03.290
"The Goldilocks Zone Is For Idiots:

194
00:13:03.357 --> 00:13:05.827
Why Everyone Is Wrong About Life."

195
00:13:06.293 --> 00:13:07.662
That was a long time ago.

196
00:13:07.729 --> 00:13:08.949
Do you stand by what you wrote?

197
00:13:08.973 --> 00:13:11.699
I was fired for standing by what I wrote.

198
00:13:11.766 --> 00:13:13.233
You were fired

199
00:13:13.300 --> 00:13:15.235
for calling the leading
scholar in your field

200
00:13:15.302 --> 00:13:16.805
"a staggering waste of carbon"

201
00:13:16.871 --> 00:13:18.706
at the UNESCO conference in Denmark.

202
00:13:19.012 --> 00:13:21.208
You heard about that. huh?

203
00:13:21.275 --> 00:13:23.678
Look. I don't know what this is.

204
00:13:23.745 --> 00:13:26.714
but. uh. I think I'm not s...

205
00:13:26.781 --> 00:13:27.948
That's lava.

206
00:13:28.015 --> 00:13:29.616
- It's not.
- Okay.

207
00:13:29.684 --> 00:13:32.052
No one in your field
wants anything to do with you

208
00:13:32.119 --> 00:13:33.396
because you refused to back down

209
00:13:33.420 --> 00:13:35.255
from a very unpopular view.

210
00:13:35.322 --> 00:13:36.834
and I can give you a chance
to prove them all wrong.

211
00:13:36.858 --> 00:13:38.793
Uh Kevin. no running.

212
00:13:38.860 --> 00:13:40.461
[Kevin] I'm not.

213
00:13:40.527 --> 00:13:43.731
Well. joke's on them because
I don't even care. So.

214
00:13:44.866 --> 00:13:46.333
[Stratt] I think you do care.

215
00:13:46.400 --> 00:13:48.040
You're running away
because you're scared.

216
00:13:48.068 --> 00:13:49.603
[Grace] No. I'm not.

217
00:13:51.104 --> 00:13:52.504
[Stratt] Do you still believe water

218
00:13:52.539 --> 00:13:54.441
is unnecessary for life to evolve?

219
00:13:54.508 --> 00:13:55.677
[Grace] Uh.

220
00:13:56.076 --> 00:13:59.613
Look. there is nothing magical
about hydrogen and oxygen.

221
00:13:59.681 --> 00:14:02.149
Water is required for life on Earth. sure.

222
00:14:02.216 --> 00:14:03.718
But a completely different planet

223
00:14:03.785 --> 00:14:05.428
might have completely
different conditions.

224
00:14:05.452 --> 00:14:07.092
I don't know why
that makes me such a nut.

225
00:14:07.120 --> 00:14:09.089
I need you to come with us.

226
00:14:10.257 --> 00:14:11.501
Sorry. I didn't catch your name.

227
00:14:11.525 --> 00:14:12.593
Carl.

228
00:14:12.660 --> 00:14:14.328
- Carl. Hi.
- [Stratt] Dr. Grace.

229
00:14:14.394 --> 00:14:15.749
Petrova line samples
splashed down last night.

230
00:14:15.773 --> 00:14:19.166
I want you to tell me
what they are. how they work.

231
00:14:19.233 --> 00:14:22.069
I am a teacher
at Grover Cleveland Middle.

232
00:14:22.135 --> 00:14:23.814
And you have a doctorate
in molecular biology.

233
00:14:23.838 --> 00:14:27.842
And I ride a bike to work.
and it's not for exercise.

234
00:14:27.909 --> 00:14:29.149
So I'm sure there are thousands

235
00:14:29.209 --> 00:14:30.116
of other people who are better...

236
00:14:30.141 --> 00:14:31.942
It survives on the surface of the sun.

237
00:14:31.967 --> 00:14:34.007
Does that sound like
a water-based life form to you?

238
00:14:41.255 --> 00:14:42.790
The sun's really dying. isn't it?

239
00:14:42.857 --> 00:14:44.491
Yeah.

240
00:14:45.994 --> 00:14:47.361
[machinery whirring]

241
00:14:48.440 --> 00:14:51.576
Is all of this necessary?

242
00:14:51.933 --> 00:14:52.851
[switch clicks]

243
00:14:52.876 --> 00:14:54.278
[Stratt] Yes.

244
00:14:54.366 --> 00:14:56.999
<i>Please analyze the Petrova sample.</i>

245
00:14:57.024 --> 00:14:58.338
[Grace] Um.

246
00:14:58.405 --> 00:14:59.974
[Stratt] <i>Just one thing.</i>

247
00:15:00.040 --> 00:15:01.251
The entire room is filled with argon.

248
00:15:01.275 --> 00:15:03.110
Just try not to rip your suit.

249
00:15:03.873 --> 00:15:05.275
[Grace] Uh.

250
00:15:07.303 --> 00:15:09.918
Am I expendable?
Is that why you want me?

251
00:15:09.984 --> 00:15:11.686
That's not the only reason.

252
00:15:11.711 --> 00:15:14.054
It's almost like you don't care if I die.

253
00:15:14.121 --> 00:15:15.657
[chuckles nervously]

254
00:15:18.525 --> 00:15:21.061
Hold on. You have to talk about it?

255
00:15:21.393 --> 00:15:22.994
The consensus here

256
00:15:23.019 --> 00:15:25.888
is that it would be preferable
if you did not die.

257
00:15:27.234 --> 00:15:28.378
[sarcastically] Thanks. guys.

258
00:15:28.402 --> 00:15:31.405
[soft intriguing music playing]

259
00:15:35.609 --> 00:15:37.344
- Oh.
- [container whirring]

260
00:15:40.113 --> 00:15:41.783
[whirring]

261
00:15:42.282 --> 00:15:44.652
Welcome to Earth.

262
00:15:56.396 --> 00:15:57.699
[exhales sharply]

263
00:15:58.911 --> 00:16:01.046
- [switch clicks]
- [Stratt] Are they alive?

264
00:16:01.268 --> 00:16:02.502
[Grace] They're moving.

265
00:16:02.569 --> 00:16:04.104
[Stratt] So they're alive.

266
00:16:04.171 --> 00:16:05.673
[sputters] Yes. they're moving.

267
00:16:05.740 --> 00:16:07.909
but that could be for many reasons.

268
00:16:07.976 --> 00:16:09.509
What are they made of?

269
00:16:09.576 --> 00:16:11.578
It's gonna take a long ti...
It took like 200 years

270
00:16:11.645 --> 00:16:13.748
to figure out how bacteria works. so.

271
00:16:13.815 --> 00:16:15.649
Please do it faster.

272
00:16:17.719 --> 00:16:20.722
[Grace] I'm just going through
the whole light spectrum here.

273
00:16:21.257 --> 00:16:22.458
Wow!

274
00:16:24.092 --> 00:16:26.126
You're not gonna believe this.

275
00:16:28.613 --> 00:16:29.913
Nothing happened.

276
00:16:34.725 --> 00:16:37.295
I can't see into these buggers.

277
00:16:39.473 --> 00:16:40.808
Amazing.

278
00:16:40.875 --> 00:16:44.712
X-rays. microwaves.
gamma rays. visible light.

279
00:16:44.779 --> 00:16:46.413
Nothing!

280
00:16:47.715 --> 00:16:50.918
Ooh. ooh. ooh. I've been
dying to do this all day!

281
00:16:56.758 --> 00:16:58.291
[music stops]

282
00:17:03.163 --> 00:17:04.666
[music resumes]

283
00:17:07.735 --> 00:17:09.070
It's a cell!

284
00:17:09.137 --> 00:17:11.571
It's a cell. Wake up! It's a cell!

285
00:17:11.630 --> 00:17:14.901
[Grace] It's a tiny alien cell.
You guys! [Chuckles]

286
00:17:14.976 --> 00:17:16.343
Applause.

287
00:17:16.410 --> 00:17:19.546
[Grace] Guys! This is first contact!

288
00:17:20.048 --> 00:17:22.850
With life outside of the...!

289
00:17:23.350 --> 00:17:24.752
- [music stops]
- Uh-oh.

290
00:17:25.185 --> 00:17:26.520
Oh. it died.

291
00:17:26.586 --> 00:17:28.355
- [switch clicks]
- [Stratt] What?

292
00:17:29.356 --> 00:17:30.825
This is great news.

293
00:17:30.892 --> 00:17:33.193
Now we can find out
what they're made of.

294
00:17:33.995 --> 00:17:35.429
[music resumes]

295
00:17:35.495 --> 00:17:37.431
You guys fired up?

296
00:17:40.295 --> 00:17:41.729
Yes!

297
00:17:42.016 --> 00:17:43.219
Right?

298
00:17:44.172 --> 00:17:45.773
Carbon.

299
00:17:46.165 --> 00:17:47.866
Oxygen.

300
00:17:50.048 --> 00:17:51.817
Hydrogen.

301
00:17:52.212 --> 00:17:53.715
- [music stops]
- Oh.

302
00:17:55.382 --> 00:17:57.919
[somber music playing]

303
00:18:07.787 --> 00:18:09.622
It's made

304
00:18:10.732 --> 00:18:11.766
[music fades]

305
00:18:11.833 --> 00:18:13.835
almost entirely

306
00:18:15.568 --> 00:18:17.236
of water.

307
00:18:26.550 --> 00:18:28.652
- All right.
- [Grace exhales]

308
00:18:30.785 --> 00:18:33.154
Sorry if I overreacted in there.

309
00:18:33.654 --> 00:18:36.289
Just. uh. realizing I was wrong

310
00:18:36.356 --> 00:18:38.226
about the only original idea I ever had.

311
00:18:38.291 --> 00:18:39.927
Yeah. What else did you learn?

312
00:18:39.994 --> 00:18:42.262
They give off infrared light
when they move.

313
00:18:42.329 --> 00:18:43.330
[Stratt] Mm-hm.

314
00:18:43.396 --> 00:18:44.126
Like. so much.

315
00:18:44.150 --> 00:18:45.939
I don't know how
they store all that energy.

316
00:18:45.964 --> 00:18:50.634
But. uh. their wavelength is
exactly the Petrova frequency.

317
00:18:51.612 --> 00:18:52.931
The light is how they move.

318
00:18:52.956 --> 00:18:55.176
Yeah. they consume the sun's energy.

319
00:18:55.243 --> 00:18:57.344
and then they expel it for propulsion.

320
00:18:57.410 --> 00:18:59.446
They toot to scoot basically.

321
00:19:00.939 --> 00:19:03.383
Why did it go to Venus?

322
00:19:04.564 --> 00:19:06.131
I don't know.

323
00:19:07.887 --> 00:19:09.257
Okay. We'll tell you.

324
00:19:09.322 --> 00:19:10.758
What?

325
00:19:10.825 --> 00:19:13.326
I have 347 other biologists
in 21 countries

326
00:19:13.393 --> 00:19:15.029
mobilizing as we speak.

327
00:19:15.096 --> 00:19:17.564
So thank you for your help.
I'm glad you didn't die.

328
00:19:17.631 --> 00:19:18.900
Let's pack this up.

329
00:19:18.966 --> 00:19:20.701
- [doors whirring]
- [man] Pack up!

330
00:19:20.768 --> 00:19:23.370
- [indistinct radio chatter]
- [helicopter hovering]

331
00:19:23.436 --> 00:19:25.173
[Grace] That's it?

332
00:19:25.239 --> 00:19:27.041
- That's it. Carl?
- Talk to her.

333
00:19:27.108 --> 00:19:28.408
You're taking all the stuff?

334
00:19:28.475 --> 00:19:30.211
At the school you said

335
00:19:30.278 --> 00:19:32.122
there were thousands of people
more qualified than you. so

336
00:19:32.146 --> 00:19:34.414
- I was being modest.
- [Stratt] I don't need modest.

337
00:19:34.481 --> 00:19:35.961
I need people who think they're right

338
00:19:36.017 --> 00:19:37.652
when everyone else
thinks they're wrong.

339
00:19:37.718 --> 00:19:39.196
I need people who piss other people off.

340
00:19:39.220 --> 00:19:40.320
That's me!

341
00:19:40.387 --> 00:19:42.156
Do you want to be on a project?

342
00:19:42.223 --> 00:19:44.324
If you.

343
00:19:44.391 --> 00:19:47.360
If you think I can help. then.

344
00:19:47.427 --> 00:19:49.396
Just answer the question.

345
00:19:49.462 --> 00:19:51.364
I wanna help the world.

346
00:19:51.431 --> 00:19:53.000
I left you three dots.

347
00:19:53.067 --> 00:19:54.401
Just three. huh?

348
00:19:54.467 --> 00:19:56.037
Plus the one you killed.

349
00:19:56.314 --> 00:19:58.016
I would take the three.

350
00:20:00.270 --> 00:20:01.872
- [Stratt] Yes?
- I'll take the dots.

351
00:20:01.976 --> 00:20:03.679
Get to work. Dr. Grace.

352
00:20:05.193 --> 00:20:07.663
The world is counting on you.

353
00:20:08.082 --> 00:20:09.817
[ethereal chorus vocalizing]

354
00:21:07.708 --> 00:21:09.010
[inhales sharply]

355
00:21:11.379 --> 00:21:12.680
[music fades]

356
00:21:15.195 --> 00:21:16.730
[Grace] <i>Hey. Carl?</i>

357
00:21:17.936 --> 00:21:19.136
[Carl] This is Carl.

358
00:21:19.202 --> 00:21:20.772
[Grace] Imagine for a second

359
00:21:20.838 --> 00:21:23.308
that you're an interstellar microorganism.

360
00:21:23.374 --> 00:21:25.443
[Carl] I'm not doing that.

361
00:21:26.811 --> 00:21:29.681
[Grace] Why would you
leave the sun and go to Venus?

362
00:21:29.747 --> 00:21:32.750
Why not stop at Mercury? It's closer.

363
00:21:34.084 --> 00:21:35.820
Maybe fresh air?

364
00:21:35.887 --> 00:21:37.956
[Grace] Venus's atmosphere
is mostly CO2.

365
00:21:38.022 --> 00:21:39.624
Maybe that's fresh air to them.

366
00:21:39.691 --> 00:21:41.759
You don't know what
these little space dots like.

367
00:21:46.898 --> 00:21:48.032
[Grace] <i>Hey. Carl?</i>

368
00:21:48.309 --> 00:21:49.934
Do we have an expense account?

369
00:21:50.001 --> 00:21:51.836
We don't.

370
00:21:52.604 --> 00:21:53.805
[purses lips]

371
00:21:54.939 --> 00:21:55.940
[sighs deeply]

372
00:21:56.007 --> 00:21:57.342
But I do.

373
00:21:58.309 --> 00:22:00.210
[afro-pop dance song playing]

374
00:22:02.480 --> 00:22:04.582
[indistinct announcement over PA]

375
00:22:28.506 --> 00:22:30.441
[Carl] All right. I got something for you.

376
00:22:32.777 --> 00:22:34.646
[scanner beeping]

377
00:22:39.182 --> 00:22:40.918
[scanner beeping]

378
00:22:40.985 --> 00:22:42.453
Thank you.

379
00:22:42.520 --> 00:22:44.197
- Do you have a coupon?
- We don't need a coupon.

380
00:22:44.221 --> 00:22:46.004
- We're the government.
- Which government?

381
00:22:46.030 --> 00:22:47.565
All of 'em.

382
00:22:49.535 --> 00:22:50.928
So this box is Venus.

383
00:22:50.995 --> 00:22:52.597
The box is Venus.

384
00:22:52.664 --> 00:22:54.832
It's set to emit the same
infrared light frequency

385
00:22:54.899 --> 00:22:56.567
as Venus's CO2 atmosphere.

386
00:22:56.634 --> 00:22:58.770
So if the dots move
when you turn the lights on.

387
00:22:58.836 --> 00:23:01.506
that means they're looking for CO2.

388
00:23:01.572 --> 00:23:04.108
Thus proving the Carl Hypothesis.

389
00:23:04.174 --> 00:23:05.175
[Carl] Sick.

390
00:23:05.242 --> 00:23:06.285
[drill whirring]

391
00:23:07.264 --> 00:23:08.664
Sorry.

392
00:23:08.808 --> 00:23:10.029
- [Grace] All right.
- [Carl] All right.

393
00:23:10.053 --> 00:23:11.822
[Grace] You ready?

394
00:23:15.319 --> 00:23:17.187
Uh-oh.

395
00:23:17.254 --> 00:23:18.723
Why you saying "Uh-oh"?

396
00:23:18.790 --> 00:23:20.858
[Grace] The Astrophage
moved off the slide.

397
00:23:20.925 --> 00:23:22.093
[Carl] Huh?

398
00:23:22.160 --> 00:23:23.695
We lost them.

399
00:23:23.761 --> 00:23:25.897
[Carl] What do you mean.
we lost them? Go get them.

400
00:23:26.263 --> 00:23:27.865
If I open the door in the light.

401
00:23:27.932 --> 00:23:30.101
they're gonna escape. and then
we'll lose them forever.

402
00:23:30.168 --> 00:23:31.502
At least now they're in the box.

403
00:23:31.569 --> 00:23:33.504
So we'll just turn the lights off.

404
00:23:33.571 --> 00:23:34.757
But there'll still be light.
It's gotta be total darkness.

405
00:23:34.781 --> 00:23:37.540
Okay. so just put this box in another box.

406
00:23:45.983 --> 00:23:47.385
Nice.

407
00:23:56.027 --> 00:23:57.995
[whirring]

408
00:23:58.801 --> 00:24:01.238
[Grace] Go ahead and close it. Over.

409
00:24:01.629 --> 00:24:03.297
[Carl] I can hear you.

410
00:24:07.004 --> 00:24:08.436
[drill whirring]

411
00:24:08.739 --> 00:24:11.009
[Grace] Entering phase two.

412
00:24:12.244 --> 00:24:14.012
[drill whirring]

413
00:24:16.414 --> 00:24:17.949
I'm in.

414
00:24:23.182 --> 00:24:25.318
[Carl on radio] <i>Please report. Over.</i>

415
00:24:27.791 --> 00:24:29.461
[Grace] <i>There's one.</i>

416
00:24:30.862 --> 00:24:31.963
<i>There's two!</i>

417
00:24:32.030 --> 00:24:34.266
Come on! Get the third one.

418
00:24:36.134 --> 00:24:37.902
[Grace] <i>Got sample three.</i>

419
00:24:37.969 --> 00:24:40.205
<i>The Three Musketeers.
The Three Stooges.</i>

420
00:24:43.774 --> 00:24:44.943
<i>Uh-oh.</i>

421
00:24:45.010 --> 00:24:47.012
[Carl] What? What?

422
00:24:47.912 --> 00:24:49.681
[Grace] <i>Are you sitting down?</i>

423
00:24:49.748 --> 00:24:51.349
No. I'm standing like a grown man.

424
00:24:51.826 --> 00:24:53.918
[Grace] <i>'Cause there's a fourth.</i>

425
00:24:54.552 --> 00:24:55.854
What?

426
00:24:57.689 --> 00:25:00.158
[Grace] <i>We're fathers. Carl.</i>

427
00:25:02.193 --> 00:25:04.496
[Carl] Now I'm sitting down.

428
00:25:05.664 --> 00:25:07.032
[line ringing]

429
00:25:07.397 --> 00:25:08.397
[Stratt] <i>Stratt.</i>

430
00:25:08.662 --> 00:25:11.336
Carl and I made a baby.

431
00:25:11.606 --> 00:25:12.804
[Stratt] <i>What?</i>

432
00:25:12.871 --> 00:25:14.673
We figured out how Astrophage breeds.

433
00:25:14.739 --> 00:25:15.807
[thudding]

434
00:25:15.874 --> 00:25:17.409
[Stratt] <i>Don't move.</i>

435
00:25:19.311 --> 00:25:20.812
Wheels up.

436
00:25:21.846 --> 00:25:23.257
- [tires screeching]
- [Grace] You know. Carl.

437
00:25:23.281 --> 00:25:25.517
when Stratt said she was sending a jet.

438
00:25:25.583 --> 00:25:27.261
I thought you meant
like a PJ or something.

439
00:25:27.285 --> 00:25:30.322
- [Carl] I know.
- [officer] Take this.

440
00:25:31.456 --> 00:25:33.091
Been a long time since I've taken a pill

441
00:25:33.158 --> 00:25:34.735
from a stranger
without knowing what it was.

442
00:25:34.759 --> 00:25:36.861
[engine roaring]

443
00:25:36.928 --> 00:25:38.963
Oh my God! Stop!

444
00:25:39.030 --> 00:25:41.166
[grunting]

445
00:25:42.701 --> 00:25:44.135
[jet thuds]

446
00:25:49.341 --> 00:25:51.409
[Stratt] Dr. Grace. how was your flight?

447
00:25:51.476 --> 00:25:52.577
[indistinct chatter]

448
00:25:56.715 --> 00:25:58.483
- [Grace] Where are we?
- [Stratt] The ocean.

449
00:25:58.550 --> 00:26:01.453
The Astrophage reproduction.
Can you do it at scale?

450
00:26:01.519 --> 00:26:05.590
Oh. in theory. you just get
a bunch of elbow-shaped pipe.

451
00:26:05.657 --> 00:26:06.958
put sunlight in one end...

452
00:26:07.025 --> 00:26:08.360
Excuse me for a second.

453
00:26:08.426 --> 00:26:09.728
[Grace retching]

454
00:26:09.794 --> 00:26:11.138
- Write it down.
- [Aide] Yes. ma'am.

455
00:26:11.162 --> 00:26:12.630
[Grace clears throat]

456
00:26:12.697 --> 00:26:15.667
and IR light and CO2
in the other. Repeat.

457
00:26:15.734 --> 00:26:16.877
Anything else you need for...

458
00:26:16.901 --> 00:26:18.436
[Grace] Just some water.

459
00:26:18.503 --> 00:26:19.847
He gave me a pill
and it's still in my throat.

460
00:26:19.871 --> 00:26:21.172
[officer] Two venti coffees.

461
00:26:21.239 --> 00:26:22.741
Thank you so much. Water for him.

462
00:26:22.808 --> 00:26:23.908
Or coffee. That's

463
00:26:23.975 --> 00:26:25.477
I need both.

464
00:26:25.543 --> 00:26:26.945
Or not.

465
00:26:27.011 --> 00:26:28.189
Okay. so this is kind of a tough room.

466
00:26:28.213 --> 00:26:29.849
so don't take it personally.

467
00:26:29.914 --> 00:26:31.383
I don't need anything fancy.

468
00:26:31.449 --> 00:26:34.018
As long as there's a bed
and a shower I'm good.

469
00:26:35.920 --> 00:26:37.188
[chatter fades]

470
00:26:38.523 --> 00:26:40.468
- [softly] I can't do this.
- [Stratt] Come on. Yes.

471
00:26:40.492 --> 00:26:42.370
- [Grace] I can't. I can't.
- [Stratt] You're doing great.

472
00:26:42.394 --> 00:26:44.763
Everyone. this is Dr. Ryland Grace

473
00:26:44.830 --> 00:26:46.064
from the United States.

474
00:26:46.131 --> 00:26:48.299
Please go here. Thank you.

475
00:26:48.366 --> 00:26:51.536
And he figured out
how to breed Astrophage.

476
00:26:56.876 --> 00:26:58.376
How did you do it?

477
00:26:58.443 --> 00:27:00.121
[Dr. Lokken] How long
does the process take?

478
00:27:00.145 --> 00:27:02.280
Does it reproduce by mitosis or meiosis?

479
00:27:02.347 --> 00:27:04.749
[scientist over monitor]
<i>What is the incubation period?</i>

480
00:27:04.817 --> 00:27:05.917
[overlapping chatter]

481
00:27:05.984 --> 00:27:07.752
[Grace] Um [clears throat]

482
00:27:08.854 --> 00:27:11.723
Carl and I made a mini Venus
out of a plywood box.

483
00:27:12.123 --> 00:27:14.426
and as soon as the samples recognized

484
00:27:14.492 --> 00:27:17.996
the. uh. spectral signature
of CO2. they were.

485
00:27:19.964 --> 00:27:21.801
They were like. "Whoomp! There it is!"

486
00:27:21.867 --> 00:27:22.934
Okay.

487
00:27:23.001 --> 00:27:24.602
You can sit down.

488
00:27:25.092 --> 00:27:26.171
[Narender] Who's Carl?

489
00:27:26.237 --> 00:27:27.748
While your experiment
was crude and clumsy.

490
00:27:27.772 --> 00:27:30.108
our scientists have replicated his results.

491
00:27:30.175 --> 00:27:31.576
[indistinct chatter]

492
00:27:32.655 --> 00:27:34.679
I'm sorry. how did you see...?

493
00:27:34.746 --> 00:27:36.781
We estimate an eight-day doubling time

494
00:27:36.849 --> 00:27:38.049
under optimal conditions.

495
00:27:38.116 --> 00:27:40.485
- Dr. Grace is right.
- Oh.

496
00:27:40.552 --> 00:27:41.986
It is the CO2.

497
00:27:42.053 --> 00:27:43.431
[softly] That's why
they're going to Venus.

498
00:27:43.455 --> 00:27:44.956
Please say it for everyone.

499
00:27:45.023 --> 00:27:46.383
That's why they're going to Venus.

500
00:27:46.424 --> 00:27:49.360
So that's why they're going to Venus.

501
00:27:49.427 --> 00:27:51.262
is what Dr. Grace wants to say.

502
00:27:51.329 --> 00:27:52.940
[in normal voice] They're going to breed.

503
00:27:52.964 --> 00:27:54.834
Whoomp! There it is.

504
00:27:54.900 --> 00:27:56.468
[Grace chuckles]

505
00:27:56.534 --> 00:27:58.169
I really like him.

506
00:27:58.236 --> 00:28:00.806
How long to make two million kilogram?

507
00:28:00.873 --> 00:28:02.540
Two million?

508
00:28:04.175 --> 00:28:05.510
Two million is...

509
00:28:05.577 --> 00:28:06.711
Why

510
00:28:08.279 --> 00:28:10.748
on earth would you need
that much Astrophage?

511
00:28:10.816 --> 00:28:13.151
Nobody told him?

512
00:28:13.618 --> 00:28:14.752
He has no clearance.

513
00:28:14.820 --> 00:28:16.754
Please stand up. Dr. Grace.

514
00:28:17.489 --> 00:28:18.656
Stand up.

515
00:28:19.424 --> 00:28:21.259
I hereby grant you top-secret clearance

516
00:28:21.326 --> 00:28:24.162
to all information pertaining
to Project Hail Mary.

517
00:28:25.129 --> 00:28:27.065
[softly] What's Project Hail Mary?

518
00:28:28.700 --> 00:28:30.001
[Stratt] All right.

519
00:28:33.037 --> 00:28:35.406
The sun is not the only star dying.

520
00:28:35.473 --> 00:28:37.709
There is a clear pattern of infection.

521
00:28:37.775 --> 00:28:41.881
Every star was infected
by its neighbor except one.

522
00:28:41.947 --> 00:28:43.314
Tau Ceti?

523
00:28:43.381 --> 00:28:45.016
That's right. 11.9 light years away.

524
00:28:45.083 --> 00:28:46.784
It is uninfected

525
00:28:46.852 --> 00:28:48.930
despite being well within
the cluster of infected stars.

526
00:28:48.954 --> 00:28:49.955
Why?

527
00:28:50.054 --> 00:28:51.155
Why? Tell him.

528
00:28:51.222 --> 00:28:52.624
[all in unison] We don't know!

529
00:28:52.690 --> 00:28:55.059
Which is why we decided to build a ship

530
00:28:55.126 --> 00:28:56.862
to go there and find out.

531
00:28:56.929 --> 00:28:58.329
It's 11.9 light years away.

532
00:28:58.396 --> 00:29:00.833
You can't just build an interstellar ship.

533
00:29:00.900 --> 00:29:02.166
Oh yeah. we can.

534
00:29:02.233 --> 00:29:03.802
The ship is not really the problem.

535
00:29:03.869 --> 00:29:07.205
The energy required to power
the ship is the problem.

536
00:29:07.272 --> 00:29:08.640
It was the problem.

537
00:29:10.553 --> 00:29:12.303
The Astrophage is the fuel.

538
00:29:12.328 --> 00:29:14.345
Provided we can make enough of it.

539
00:29:14.412 --> 00:29:17.382
And for that. we need you. my friend.

540
00:29:19.584 --> 00:29:20.886
Me?

541
00:29:20.953 --> 00:29:23.856
Ooh. Those little guys
store a lot of energy.

542
00:29:24.255 --> 00:29:25.891
One mistake and that much Astrophage

543
00:29:25.958 --> 00:29:28.059
could vaporize California.

544
00:29:28.126 --> 00:29:30.261
That's true. which is why
you now live on a boat

545
00:29:30.328 --> 00:29:32.096
in the middle of the ocean in case

546
00:29:32.163 --> 00:29:33.498
[imitates explosion]

547
00:29:33.565 --> 00:29:35.633
- I live on a boat?
- You do.

548
00:29:35.700 --> 00:29:38.303
So you wanna build
a near-light speed spaceship.

549
00:29:38.369 --> 00:29:40.772
have it travel further
than any human-made object

550
00:29:40.839 --> 00:29:42.140
has ever traveled.

551
00:29:42.206 --> 00:29:45.844
and visit a star just to "see what's up"?

552
00:29:46.092 --> 00:29:47.012
Yeah.

553
00:29:47.078 --> 00:29:48.646
And then what?

554
00:29:48.713 --> 00:29:50.591
[Stratt] There won't be
enough fuel for a round-trip

555
00:29:50.615 --> 00:29:54.085
so they send their findings
back to Earth on probes.

556
00:29:56.120 --> 00:29:59.157
And the astronauts

557
00:30:01.912 --> 00:30:03.467
die in space?

558
00:30:03.492 --> 00:30:04.926
Yes.

559
00:30:07.032 --> 00:30:08.801
[Grace] Space.

560
00:30:12.071 --> 00:30:14.606
Any other plans you've thought of?

561
00:30:14.672 --> 00:30:17.508
Anything else you're kicking around?

562
00:30:17.575 --> 00:30:19.945
There are infinite possibilities

563
00:30:20.012 --> 00:30:21.512
for this to go wrong.

564
00:30:21.579 --> 00:30:23.214
It almost certainly won't work.

565
00:30:23.281 --> 00:30:25.750
It's what you Americans
would call a long shot.

566
00:30:26.250 --> 00:30:27.820
Hail Mary.

567
00:30:28.119 --> 00:30:29.454
I get it now.

568
00:30:29.520 --> 00:30:33.191
The alternative is to just do nothing

569
00:30:33.758 --> 00:30:35.861
and to starve and to kill each other

570
00:30:35.928 --> 00:30:38.217
and watch everything
on this planet go extinct.

571
00:30:38.242 --> 00:30:39.743
including us.

572
00:30:40.191 --> 00:30:41.326
So.

573
00:30:50.141 --> 00:30:51.776
[pensive music playing]

574
00:31:01.820 --> 00:31:04.295
[Grace] That's a long time to be in space.

575
00:31:04.320 --> 00:31:06.491
[Stratt] They'll be in comas for most of it.

576
00:31:06.609 --> 00:31:08.176
But is that even safe?

577
00:31:08.243 --> 00:31:10.512
Nothing about this is safe.

578
00:31:25.060 --> 00:31:26.595
<i>We only need three.</i>

579
00:31:27.496 --> 00:31:28.597
<i>A pilot.</i>

580
00:31:28.664 --> 00:31:30.666
<i>An engineer.</i>

581
00:31:30.733 --> 00:31:33.168
<i>And a scientist.</i>

582
00:31:35.504 --> 00:31:36.605
[exhales sharply]

583
00:31:37.740 --> 00:31:39.475
Commander Yáo.

584
00:31:41.477 --> 00:31:44.379
I must have known you.
but I just don't remember.

585
00:31:45.080 --> 00:31:47.683
You make a funny face

586
00:31:47.750 --> 00:31:52.220
in literally every picture.

587
00:31:52.287 --> 00:31:55.390
<i>You must have been very smart</i>

588
00:31:55.458 --> 00:31:56.559
<i>and strong</i>

589
00:31:58.360 --> 00:31:59.928
and brave.

590
00:32:01.630 --> 00:32:03.031
[clears throat]

591
00:32:03.733 --> 00:32:05.033
Ilyukhina.

592
00:32:06.167 --> 00:32:08.771
First. I owe you three bags of vodka.

593
00:32:10.123 --> 00:32:12.240
<i>You seemed to have had a lot of friends.</i>

594
00:32:12.775 --> 00:32:14.175
<i>This picture of you.</i>

595
00:32:14.242 --> 00:32:17.646
what looks like sneaking into the Kremlin

596
00:32:19.381 --> 00:32:20.483
is legendary.

597
00:32:23.118 --> 00:32:25.253
<i>I wish you were still here.</i>

598
00:32:26.522 --> 00:32:28.657
<i>I wish I wasn't alone.</i>

599
00:32:28.724 --> 00:32:30.626
I wish I was

600
00:32:31.477 --> 00:32:33.945
doing a better job. I just. uh.

601
00:32:38.584 --> 00:32:40.752
You were both very loved.

602
00:32:41.152 --> 00:32:42.287
[sniffles]

603
00:32:42.355 --> 00:32:43.822
You deserve much more than this.

604
00:32:46.224 --> 00:32:47.826
[voice breaking] I'll do my best

605
00:32:47.892 --> 00:32:49.794
to make sure that you don't

606
00:32:50.663 --> 00:32:51.663
[sniffles]

607
00:32:51.755 --> 00:32:54.025
you know. that you didn't...

608
00:33:00.339 --> 00:33:01.840
[sniffles]

609
00:33:02.941 --> 00:33:04.809
[clears throat]

610
00:33:06.278 --> 00:33:08.046
I'll do my best.

611
00:33:19.824 --> 00:33:21.460
[pensive music rises]

612
00:33:54.360 --> 00:33:56.227
[birds chirping]

613
00:34:08.808 --> 00:34:10.208
[music fades]

614
00:34:11.009 --> 00:34:12.478
[alarm blaring]

615
00:34:13.211 --> 00:34:15.548
[Mary] <i>Approaching Tau Ceti orbit.</i>

616
00:34:15.614 --> 00:34:16.848
<i>Prepare for engine cutoff.</i>

617
00:34:16.915 --> 00:34:18.317
[tense music playing]

618
00:34:18.384 --> 00:34:19.984
<i>Fourteen. thirteen</i>
-[Grace] What?

619
00:34:20.051 --> 00:34:21.520
Why engine cutoff?

620
00:34:21.587 --> 00:34:24.155
Seems like something
we should talk about.

621
00:34:24.222 --> 00:34:25.957
[Mary] <i>Pilot detected.</i>

622
00:34:26.024 --> 00:34:28.093
- [systems powering up]
- What? No. I'm not a pilot!

623
00:34:28.159 --> 00:34:29.729
[Mary] <i>Four. three.</i>

624
00:34:29.795 --> 00:34:32.030
What happens at zero? I mean...

625
00:34:34.866 --> 00:34:36.167
[music fades]

626
00:34:39.672 --> 00:34:41.940
<i>You are now orbiting Tau Ceti.</i>

627
00:34:42.006 --> 00:34:44.876
- [intriguing music playing]
- [shrieking]

628
00:34:44.943 --> 00:34:48.714
What the fudging fudger?

629
00:34:48.781 --> 00:34:50.248
[Grace grunting]

630
00:34:51.350 --> 00:34:53.753
[Mary] <i>Petrov a scope operational.</i>

631
00:34:53.819 --> 00:34:56.121
<i>Petrov a scope operational.</i>

632
00:35:17.008 --> 00:35:18.377
It's Tau Ceti.

633
00:35:29.087 --> 00:35:31.624
You have a Petrova line.

634
00:35:31.954 --> 00:35:33.559
But you're not dimming.

635
00:35:33.626 --> 00:35:35.628
Why?

636
00:35:45.406 --> 00:35:47.007
What is that?

637
00:36:04.390 --> 00:36:06.492
[Mary] <i>Blip-A detected.</i>

638
00:36:07.158 --> 00:36:09.528
What's a Blip-A?

639
00:36:09.595 --> 00:36:12.096
[Mary] <i>Blip-A detected.</i>

640
00:36:25.411 --> 00:36:28.046
[intriguing music continues]

641
00:37:12.758 --> 00:37:14.326
[music fades]

642
00:37:16.595 --> 00:37:20.064
No. no. No. no. no.
Let's go. Let's go. Mary.

643
00:37:20.131 --> 00:37:21.767
No-No-No-No!

644
00:37:21.834 --> 00:37:22.968
Pilot detected!

645
00:37:23.034 --> 00:37:24.503
[Mary] <i>Please engage restraint.</i>

646
00:37:24.570 --> 00:37:25.971
Pilot detected!

647
00:37:26.037 --> 00:37:27.749
- [Mary] <i>Pilot detected.</i>
- We're getting outta here.

648
00:37:27.773 --> 00:37:29.341
[Mary] <i>Engage spin drive.</i>

649
00:37:29.408 --> 00:37:31.544
- Engage the spin drive.
- [Mary] <i>Incorrect.</i>

650
00:37:31.610 --> 00:37:33.111
<i>Welcome to the</i> Hail Mary.

651
00:37:33.177 --> 00:37:34.647
Is it this thing?

652
00:37:35.915 --> 00:37:38.116
[amusing music playing]

653
00:37:39.307 --> 00:37:42.210
[Mary] <i>Erratic maneuver detected.</i>

654
00:37:44.222 --> 00:37:45.491
Yeah.

655
00:37:52.765 --> 00:37:55.066
- [music stops]
- [exhales sharply]

656
00:37:58.971 --> 00:38:00.573
[music resumes]

657
00:38:01.482 --> 00:38:03.317
[Mary] <i>Blip-A detected.</i>

658
00:38:04.075 --> 00:38:05.744
[Grace groans]

659
00:38:05.811 --> 00:38:07.813
What do they want?

660
00:38:21.727 --> 00:38:23.161
[music stops]

661
00:38:24.697 --> 00:38:27.800
[thrumming]

662
00:38:38.043 --> 00:38:39.345
What?

663
00:38:41.245 --> 00:38:44.115
[amusing music playing]

664
00:38:49.021 --> 00:38:50.589
[grunts]

665
00:38:52.551 --> 00:38:53.984
[Mary] <i>Blip-B detected.</i>

666
00:38:54.009 --> 00:38:54.790
What's a Bl...?

667
00:38:54.815 --> 00:38:57.900
[Mary] <i>Current distance</i>
<i>from</i> Hail Mary <i>is 800 meters.</i>

668
00:38:58.162 --> 00:39:00.499
It's sending me something.

669
00:39:02.434 --> 00:39:04.603
It could be a message.

670
00:39:07.106 --> 00:39:09.240
It could be a bomb.

671
00:39:09.481 --> 00:39:10.616
Is it a bomb?

672
00:39:12.344 --> 00:39:14.013
Shields up!

673
00:39:14.079 --> 00:39:15.122
<i>There are no shields</i>
<i>on board the</i> Hail Mary.

674
00:39:15.146 --> 00:39:16.515
Why not?

675
00:39:16.582 --> 00:39:18.216
<i>- Thirty meters.</i>
- [music intensifies]

676
00:39:18.282 --> 00:39:21.152
<i>Twenty meters. Ten.</i>

677
00:39:22.688 --> 00:39:23.856
[music fades]

678
00:39:29.293 --> 00:39:30.863
[exhales deeply]

679
00:39:31.131 --> 00:39:34.833
Well. I guess there's egg
on both our faces. huh. Mary?

680
00:39:35.084 --> 00:39:38.137
- [Mary] <i>Blip-C detected.</i>
- What's that?

681
00:39:38.202 --> 00:39:40.372
[amusing music playing]

682
00:39:41.068 --> 00:39:44.004
Why is it moving so much
slower than the last one?

683
00:39:48.313 --> 00:39:49.882
They think I'm dumb.

684
00:39:54.053 --> 00:39:56.489
If we were gonna catch it.
what would we do?

685
00:39:56.555 --> 00:39:59.791
[Mary] <i>Would you like to go</i>
<i>on a space walk. Dr. Grace?</i>

686
00:40:01.527 --> 00:40:03.396
[exhales. clicks tongue]

687
00:40:05.298 --> 00:40:07.199
[Mary] <i>To begin your space walk.</i>

688
00:40:07.266 --> 00:40:10.835
<i>put on your EVA suit
and proceed to the airlock.</i>

689
00:40:20.879 --> 00:40:22.448
[Grace] Yeah.

690
00:40:22.515 --> 00:40:24.183
Yes!

691
00:40:27.253 --> 00:40:28.387
[grunts]

692
00:40:29.255 --> 00:40:31.090
[groans]

693
00:40:32.857 --> 00:40:35.227
[beeping]

694
00:40:41.000 --> 00:40:42.368
[music fades]

695
00:40:42.435 --> 00:40:43.536
[breathing deeply]

696
00:40:48.507 --> 00:40:50.609
[dramatic music playing]

697
00:40:59.018 --> 00:41:00.452
No.

698
00:41:00.987 --> 00:41:02.722
That's just crazy.

699
00:41:02.789 --> 00:41:04.489
[gasps]

700
00:41:06.192 --> 00:41:08.493
[tense music playing]

701
00:41:25.477 --> 00:41:26.779
[grunts]

702
00:41:48.067 --> 00:41:50.103
[Grace panting]

703
00:42:09.756 --> 00:42:11.057
- [music stops]
- [Grace grunts]

704
00:42:11.124 --> 00:42:12.592
[Grace thuds]

705
00:42:15.561 --> 00:42:17.697
[amusing music playing]

706
00:42:26.339 --> 00:42:29.809
Righty tighty. lefty loosey.

707
00:42:31.711 --> 00:42:33.346
[spectrometer beeping]

708
00:42:35.114 --> 00:42:38.651
Xenon's a gas. I think this thing's broken.

709
00:42:44.924 --> 00:42:46.492
[Dr. Lokken] We need equipment

710
00:42:46.559 --> 00:42:49.929
to analyze the Astrophage
at Tau Ceti. Correct?

711
00:42:49.995 --> 00:42:51.506
- [Stratt] Dr. Grace.
- [Grace] Sorry. Hi.

712
00:42:51.530 --> 00:42:53.075
[Dr. Lokken] Most of
this equipment won't work

713
00:42:53.099 --> 00:42:53.962
in zero gravity.

714
00:42:53.987 --> 00:42:55.939
[Stratt] And we have a team
to develop and build

715
00:42:55.964 --> 00:42:57.704
zero gravity versions of this equipment.

716
00:42:57.820 --> 00:42:58.831
[Dr. Lokken]
We would need years for that.

717
00:42:58.855 --> 00:43:00.156
and we have months.

718
00:43:00.223 --> 00:43:01.503
[Stratt] What's the alternative?

719
00:43:01.657 --> 00:43:02.992
We make gravity.

720
00:43:03.259 --> 00:43:04.727
Centrifuge?

721
00:43:04.793 --> 00:43:06.428
Centrifuge.

722
00:43:06.495 --> 00:43:08.831
They used them to make butter
during the Civil War.

723
00:43:08.898 --> 00:43:10.132
actually.

724
00:43:10.199 --> 00:43:12.801
It's a fun fact.

725
00:43:19.308 --> 00:43:21.076
[systems powering up]

726
00:44:06.288 --> 00:44:08.524
[Mary] <i>Lab operational.</i>

727
00:44:13.929 --> 00:44:15.230
[Grace thuds]

728
00:44:18.034 --> 00:44:19.368
[spectrometer beeping]

729
00:44:21.136 --> 00:44:22.271
[Grace] Still Xenon!

730
00:44:22.871 --> 00:44:25.676
Up is down! Left is right! Xenon's a solid!

731
00:44:25.701 --> 00:44:27.235
Aliens are real!

732
00:44:27.260 --> 00:44:29.862
I'm wrong about everything
and everything's wrong.

733
00:44:30.312 --> 00:44:31.647
[exhales deeply]

734
00:44:35.051 --> 00:44:37.353
Lefty tighty. righty loosey.

735
00:44:38.454 --> 00:44:40.189
I mean... [sniffs]

736
00:44:40.255 --> 00:44:40.936
- Oh no!
- [alarm blaring]

737
00:44:40.961 --> 00:44:42.763
[Mary] <i>Foreign presence detected.</i>

738
00:44:43.926 --> 00:44:45.227
[exhales deeply]

739
00:45:06.215 --> 00:45:07.683
[object clinking]

740
00:45:07.750 --> 00:45:09.385
[Grace exclaims]

741
00:45:10.285 --> 00:45:12.321
[amusing music playing]

742
00:45:46.900 --> 00:45:49.302
You're a long way from home.

743
00:46:06.142 --> 00:46:08.477
<i>I'm a long way from home too.</i>

744
00:46:27.396 --> 00:46:29.331
[Mary] <i>Blip-D detected.</i>

745
00:47:45.374 --> 00:47:46.675
[music fades]

746
00:48:02.158 --> 00:48:03.993
[Grace breathing deeply]

747
00:48:10.933 --> 00:48:12.334
[exhales deeply]

748
00:48:12.401 --> 00:48:15.437
[grunts]

749
00:48:15.504 --> 00:48:18.440
[intriguing music playing]

750
00:48:32.421 --> 00:48:33.922
[grunts softly]

751
00:49:45.113 --> 00:49:46.382
[thuds]

752
00:49:56.239 --> 00:49:57.739
- [loud thud]
- [Grace screams]

753
00:50:01.678 --> 00:50:03.246
[Grace groans]

754
00:50:03.647 --> 00:50:04.981
[Grace panting]

755
00:50:21.831 --> 00:50:25.134
[thudding softly]

756
00:50:26.303 --> 00:50:27.471
[gasps softly]

757
00:50:31.941 --> 00:50:35.479
[soft chittering]

758
00:50:40.751 --> 00:50:42.452
Is that me?

759
00:50:54.952 --> 00:50:56.419
My ship.

760
00:51:05.776 --> 00:51:07.344
I don't understand.

761
00:51:07.411 --> 00:51:08.911
[soft chittering]

762
00:51:11.615 --> 00:51:13.082
Oh.

763
00:51:14.175 --> 00:51:16.411
You want me

764
00:51:17.554 --> 00:51:19.456
to go back in my ship?

765
00:51:20.624 --> 00:51:22.459
[soft chittering]

766
00:51:22.526 --> 00:51:23.627
But I just got here.

767
00:51:23.694 --> 00:51:25.061
[soft chittering]

768
00:51:26.623 --> 00:51:29.098
Oh. Okay.

769
00:51:29.865 --> 00:51:31.335
Okay.

770
00:51:33.637 --> 00:51:35.938
I'll talk to you later.

771
00:51:37.739 --> 00:51:38.840
Bye.

772
00:51:41.745 --> 00:51:45.014
[stirring music playing]

773
00:52:10.507 --> 00:52:13.343
[amusing music playing]

774
00:52:16.212 --> 00:52:18.515
[softly] What are they doing. Mary?

775
00:52:48.110 --> 00:52:49.846
[Mary] <i>It is not advised</i>

776
00:52:49.912 --> 00:52:51.752
<i>to modify the centrifugal
settings of the ship.</i>

777
00:52:51.782 --> 00:52:53.249
Thank you. Mary.

778
00:53:00.524 --> 00:53:02.392
[muffled thud]

779
00:53:31.421 --> 00:53:33.390
[crackling]

780
00:53:52.174 --> 00:53:54.478
[exhales sharply]

781
00:53:56.713 --> 00:53:58.147
[loud hissing]

782
00:53:59.316 --> 00:54:00.584
[groans]

783
00:54:05.020 --> 00:54:06.356
What?

784
00:54:26.354 --> 00:54:27.755
Oh my.

785
00:54:28.698 --> 00:54:30.031
This is new.

786
00:54:39.256 --> 00:54:40.590
[thudding echoes]

787
00:54:42.856 --> 00:54:44.791
Anybody home?

788
00:54:47.612 --> 00:54:51.182
I like what you've done with the gravity.

789
00:54:56.740 --> 00:54:58.608
I made you a ship.

790
00:55:03.065 --> 00:55:04.867
It's ramen.

791
