and then we'll burn up.

1541
01:36:41.096 --> 01:36:42.598
Game over.

1542
01:36:42.664 --> 01:36:43.967
Game not over.

1543
01:36:44.032 --> 01:36:45.367
I make chain. I make long chain.

1544
01:36:45.434 --> 01:36:47.536
I put collection device on end.

1545
01:36:47.603 --> 01:36:49.505
Oh. yeah. yeah.
Five kilometers of chain. Sure.

1546
01:36:49.571 --> 01:36:51.941
- Guard me!
- [Rocky] Like this chain. Look.

1547
01:36:52.007 --> 01:36:54.176
- You can do that?
- Yes.

1548
01:36:54.243 --> 01:36:55.712
Kinda like fishing.

1549
01:36:55.778 --> 01:36:57.479
[Rocky] What that?

1550
01:36:57.546 --> 01:36:58.715
Whoa. whoa!

1551
01:36:58.781 --> 01:37:01.450
[Grace] Fishing! Can you believe it?

1552
01:37:02.451 --> 01:37:05.755
- It could work.
- Thumbs up. baby.

1553
01:37:05.822 --> 01:37:06.890
Hello. Earth!

1554
01:37:06.956 --> 01:37:08.423
Plan is like fishing.

1555
01:37:08.490 --> 01:37:11.193
We get very close to Adrian atmosphere

1556
01:37:11.260 --> 01:37:13.930
and lower collector
into clouds with chain.

1557
01:37:13.997 --> 01:37:16.098
Then Grace go on hull to reel it in.

1558
01:37:16.164 --> 01:37:19.067
If ship not at precise
angle and speed. we die!

1559
01:37:19.134 --> 01:37:20.803
Example! [Thuds]

1560
01:37:20.870 --> 01:37:21.334
[exhales]

1561
01:37:21.405 --> 01:37:24.139
We must fly backwards
to keep proper velocity.

1562
01:37:24.206 --> 01:37:26.842
even though Grace
still have no pilot experience.

1563
01:37:26.992 --> 01:37:29.028
But I've been practicing. haven't I?

1564
01:37:29.094 --> 01:37:30.796
- More! No. Left. Be left.
- What?

1565
01:37:30.863 --> 01:37:33.799
More left. More left.
Is perfect. No. Wrong.

1566
01:37:33.866 --> 01:37:35.186
[Mary] <i>Erratic maneuver detected.</i>

1567
01:37:35.234 --> 01:37:36.634
[Rocky] No. Wrong way. Wrong angle.

1568
01:37:36.670 --> 01:37:37.946
Bad. bad. bad. Good. good. good.

1569
01:37:37.970 --> 01:37:39.406
Good. Bad. Not enough.

1570
01:37:39.472 --> 01:37:40.715
Not enough. Too much! Left. left. left.

1571
01:37:40.739 --> 01:37:42.141
I'm barely pulling it!

1572
01:37:42.208 --> 01:37:43.688
[Rocky] No. is bad. Grace Rocky dead.

1573
01:37:43.742 --> 01:37:45.211
All Rocky plural. all Earth. die.

1574
01:37:45.277 --> 01:37:48.347
- [Mary] <i>Power off.</i>
- [Rocky] We die. We die.

1575
01:37:49.215 --> 01:37:51.551
Rocky has built predator collector.

1576
01:37:51.618 --> 01:37:53.653
Rocky chain spooled and ready.

1577
01:37:53.719 --> 01:37:55.754
Grace pilot training not as good.

1578
01:37:56.501 --> 01:37:58.803
What think. Earth?

1579
01:38:00.287 --> 01:38:01.126
Hello?

1580
01:38:01.193 --> 01:38:03.128
- They can't hear you. pal.
- What?

1581
01:38:03.195 --> 01:38:04.806
We're not actually talking
to Earth. Earth's too far away.

1582
01:38:04.830 --> 01:38:06.165
We just record these messages

1583
01:38:06.232 --> 01:38:07.733
and we tell 'em what we've learned.

1584
01:38:07.800 --> 01:38:09.101
and then when we're done.

1585
01:38:09.168 --> 01:38:10.704
we'll send them all back in a probe.

1586
01:38:10.769 --> 01:38:12.505
[Rocky] Why not you tell them yourself

1587
01:38:12.572 --> 01:38:14.441
when you return home. question?

1588
01:38:15.842 --> 01:38:17.844
Yeah.

1589
01:38:17.911 --> 01:38:20.012
This is a one-way ticket for me. pal.

1590
01:38:20.078 --> 01:38:21.614
[Rocky] What?

1591
01:38:21.803 --> 01:38:22.991
[Grace] We had enough
Astrophage to get here

1592
01:38:23.015 --> 01:38:24.483
but not enough to get back.

1593
01:38:24.551 --> 01:38:27.219
[Rocky] So.
what happens Grace. question?

1594
01:38:27.286 --> 01:38:29.521
Oh [scoffs] I got enough food to last me

1595
01:38:29.589 --> 01:38:31.023
at least a couple years.

1596
01:38:31.089 --> 01:38:33.626
Maybe a couple more if I stretch it out.

1597
01:38:34.026 --> 01:38:36.663
[Rocky] So Grace die. question?

1598
01:38:36.729 --> 01:38:39.064
Yeah. once we're done. I'm.

1599
01:38:40.032 --> 01:38:41.433
I'm gonna die.

1600
01:38:43.335 --> 01:38:45.337
[Rocky] Why didn't you tell me?

1601
01:38:45.872 --> 01:38:47.506
[Grace] It slipped my mind.

1602
01:38:47.574 --> 01:38:50.375
[Rocky] No. Grace say Grace go home.

1603
01:38:50.442 --> 01:38:51.845
Look.

1604
01:38:51.911 --> 01:38:55.113
- Listen. Listen. Listen.
- No. No.

1605
01:38:55.489 --> 01:38:57.416
I got to meet you.

1606
01:38:57.483 --> 01:38:59.953
I got to do all this amazing stuff.

1607
01:39:00.018 --> 01:39:02.622
I'm good. I've made peace with it.

1608
01:39:03.155 --> 01:39:05.457
What mean? What mean "make peace"?

1609
01:39:05.524 --> 01:39:07.226
It means

1610
01:39:07.442 --> 01:39:10.028
I know I'm not going home

1611
01:39:10.095 --> 01:39:11.631
I know why

1612
01:39:11.698 --> 01:39:13.733
and it's okay.

1613
01:39:17.176 --> 01:39:18.551
- Thumbs up?
- No.

1614
01:39:18.576 --> 01:39:20.607
- Tiny thumbs up?
- No.

1615
01:39:21.273 --> 01:39:24.243
We got stars to save. Okay?

1616
01:39:26.378 --> 01:39:28.748
[melancholy music playing]

1617
01:39:28.815 --> 01:39:31.183
- Grace?
- Yeah.

1618
01:39:31.718 --> 01:39:33.118
You are

1619
01:39:33.185 --> 01:39:35.220
[chitters in alien language]

1620
01:39:36.623 --> 01:39:37.857
Need word.

1621
01:39:37.924 --> 01:39:39.759
W-W-What word do you need?

1622
01:39:39.826 --> 01:39:41.961
To risk self to help another.

1623
01:39:42.027 --> 01:39:43.428
Uh. dumb.

1624
01:39:43.997 --> 01:39:45.665
[Rocky] Grace?

1625
01:39:58.377 --> 01:40:00.680
[music continues]

1626
01:40:10.890 --> 01:40:13.492
How much Astrophage
you need. question?

1627
01:40:14.192 --> 01:40:16.528
[Grace] Two million kilograms.

1628
01:40:20.900 --> 01:40:22.702
[Rocky] I can give.

1629
01:40:25.872 --> 01:40:29.107
I go home six years slower.

1630
01:40:30.910 --> 01:40:32.612
That's too much.

1631
01:40:33.378 --> 01:40:35.380
Rocky watch crew die.

1632
01:40:35.815 --> 01:40:37.482
Could not fix.

1633
01:40:38.150 --> 01:40:40.319
Grace say Grace will die.

1634
01:40:40.800 --> 01:40:42.468
Rocky fix.

1635
01:40:44.122 --> 01:40:46.425
[serene music playing]

1636
01:40:58.370 --> 01:41:00.472
Grace go home.

1637
01:41:03.843 --> 01:41:05.645
[shudders]

1638
01:41:11.551 --> 01:41:12.852
Okay.

1639
01:41:17.289 --> 01:41:19.726
[music swells]

1640
01:41:34.952 --> 01:41:37.955
I thought you made peace. question?

1641
01:41:38.210 --> 01:41:41.480
I didn't mean any of that. [Sniffles]

1642
01:41:42.078 --> 01:41:44.281
That's just something you say.

1643
01:41:51.323 --> 01:41:52.859
Thank you.

1644
01:41:56.528 --> 01:41:58.831
[music crescendoes]

1645
01:42:01.199 --> 01:42:02.602
Get over here.

1646
01:42:04.737 --> 01:42:07.840
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
What? What's happening?

1647
01:42:07.907 --> 01:42:09.976
- A hug.
- Oh! Hmm.

1648
01:42:10.043 --> 01:42:13.553
It's usually not something
one does by themselves.

1649
01:42:13.578 --> 01:42:15.522
Oh. Wait. I do the same?

1650
01:42:15.823 --> 01:42:17.625
Would you just get in here?

1651
01:42:25.658 --> 01:42:28.161
How do you know when the hug is done?

1652
01:42:28.226 --> 01:42:30.529
- You just feel it.
- Oh.

1653
01:42:31.608 --> 01:42:33.198
Are you feeling it now?

1654
01:42:33.265 --> 01:42:34.266
Nope.

1655
01:42:34.332 --> 01:42:35.968
Oh. Oh. okay. Yeah.

1656
01:42:40.973 --> 01:42:43.341
[Grace] <i>We ran the sampler</i>
<i>simulation again this morning.</i>

1657
01:42:43.408 --> 01:42:45.544
Shapiro and Dubois nailed it again.

1658
01:42:45.611 --> 01:42:47.780
Okay. What about the others?

1659
01:42:48.313 --> 01:42:49.514
They'll be ready.

1660
01:42:49.582 --> 01:42:51.117
[Stratt] I expect so.

1661
01:42:51.584 --> 01:42:53.452
They have a great teacher.

1662
01:42:56.272 --> 01:42:57.707
Can you take a compliment please?

1663
01:42:57.774 --> 01:42:59.108
[Grace] No.

1664
01:42:59.174 --> 01:43:00.610
- It's an order. Okay?
- [chuckles]

1665
01:43:00.677 --> 01:43:04.414
Okay. If it's an order.
I'll take it. Thank you.

1666
01:43:04.880 --> 01:43:06.982
Good.

1667
01:43:09.101 --> 01:43:10.335
What do you think?

1668
01:43:10.403 --> 01:43:13.573
It's pretty impressive. [Sighs]

1669
01:43:14.206 --> 01:43:15.808
- Yeah.
- You're...

1670
01:43:17.075 --> 01:43:18.478
You're good.

1671
01:43:22.492 --> 01:43:24.829
- [sighs]
- Three days. huh?

1672
01:43:25.742 --> 01:43:27.142
Yeah.

1673
01:43:28.388 --> 01:43:31.791
So. what are you gonna do
for the next 20 years?

1674
01:43:31.858 --> 01:43:32.892
You got a plan?

1675
01:43:32.959 --> 01:43:34.661
[chuckles softly]

1676
01:43:37.262 --> 01:43:39.832
[distant screams]

1677
01:43:39.899 --> 01:43:41.266
[shockwave thuds]

1678
01:43:44.938 --> 01:43:47.239
[tense music playing]

1679
01:44:02.589 --> 01:44:04.557
[music swells]

1680
01:44:11.764 --> 01:44:13.098
[music calms]

1681
01:44:22.375 --> 01:44:25.344
[chair whirring softly]

1682
01:44:25.411 --> 01:44:27.814
[Mary] <i>Manual mode activated.</i>

1683
01:44:27.880 --> 01:44:29.348
[chair whirring]

1684
01:44:29.849 --> 01:44:31.351
[exhales]

1685
01:44:32.085 --> 01:44:33.419
[chitters]

1686
01:44:33.609 --> 01:44:34.710
Go.

1687
01:44:34.988 --> 01:44:37.624
[engines sputter. power up]

1688
01:44:40.026 --> 01:44:41.761
[rattling]

1689
01:44:46.666 --> 01:44:48.668
[hull creaking]

1690
01:44:54.874 --> 01:44:56.442
[engines whirring]

1691
01:44:59.211 --> 01:45:01.414
[rattling intensifies]

1692
01:45:06.019 --> 01:45:07.152
That's not half bad!

1693
01:45:07.219 --> 01:45:08.821
[Rocky] Is full good.

1694
01:45:09.989 --> 01:45:11.791
[spluttering]

1695
01:45:14.974 --> 01:45:16.477
Time go fishing. question?

1696
01:45:17.043 --> 01:45:18.811
It's now or never.

1697
01:45:19.164 --> 01:45:21.299
[whirring]

1698
01:45:21.367 --> 01:45:23.603
[suspenseful music playing]

1699
01:45:26.204 --> 01:45:28.173
[clattering]

1700
01:45:30.341 --> 01:45:31.954
- [Rocky] Three thousand meters.
- Three thousand.

1701
01:45:31.978 --> 01:45:33.479
[Rocky] Probe signal good.

1702
01:45:44.424 --> 01:45:46.392
[wind blowing]

1703
01:45:50.297 --> 01:45:51.898
Now comes the fun part.

1704
01:45:51.965 --> 01:45:53.242
[Rocky] Grace go out on hull
to retrieve collector?

1705
01:45:53.266 --> 01:45:54.267
No fun at all.

1706
01:45:54.334 --> 01:45:55.502
It's a joke.

1707
01:45:55.569 --> 01:45:58.104
[Rocky] Oh. humor. Confusing.

1708
01:46:02.976 --> 01:46:04.578
[Grace groans]

1709
01:46:04.965 --> 01:46:06.313
You gotta be kidding me.

1710
01:46:06.379 --> 01:46:07.480
What problem. question?

1711
01:46:07.547 --> 01:46:09.549
[Grace] It's fine. It's just

1712
01:46:09.616 --> 01:46:12.485
the sky is slightly on fire.

1713
01:46:13.453 --> 01:46:15.455
[spluttering]

1714
01:46:15.522 --> 01:46:16.762
[Rocky] Words of encouragement.

1715
01:46:17.357 --> 01:46:19.626
[Grace] You can't just say
"words of encouragement."

1716
01:46:20.832 --> 01:46:22.632
[Rocky on radio]
<i>Words of great encouragement.</i>

1717
01:46:22.744 --> 01:46:24.245
[Grace on radio] <i>Nope.</i>

1718
01:46:26.533 --> 01:46:28.034
[music swells]

1719
01:46:32.672 --> 01:46:34.307
[grunts]

1720
01:46:41.948 --> 01:46:43.416
[creaking]

1721
01:46:43.483 --> 01:46:45.418
[grunts]

1722
01:46:45.844 --> 01:46:48.046
- [Grace] <i>Did you feel that?</i>
- Yes.

1723
01:46:48.288 --> 01:46:50.857
I'm not worried. Are you worried?

1724
01:46:51.074 --> 01:46:52.342
[Rocky] Yes.

1725
01:46:52.409 --> 01:46:53.476
[Grace] Great.

1726
01:46:53.543 --> 01:46:55.612
[creaking continues]

1727
01:47:07.424 --> 01:47:10.026
[Rocky] Collector is closed.
Move winch into position.

1728
01:47:10.093 --> 01:47:12.195
[thudding]

1729
01:47:13.929 --> 01:47:15.598
- [firing]
- [Grace] Whoa!

1730
01:47:22.038 --> 01:47:23.673
<i>How long is this supposed to take?</i>

1731
01:47:23.740 --> 01:47:25.162
- [clangs]
- [Grace groans]

1732
01:47:25.187 --> 01:47:26.852
[Rocky on radio]
<i>Collector should be here soon.</i>

1733
01:47:26.876 --> 01:47:28.678
[Grace] Yeah. It's here.

1734
01:47:28.745 --> 01:47:30.146
[Rocky] Amaze. amaze. amaze!

1735
01:47:31.947 --> 01:47:33.583
[Grace groans]

1736
01:47:35.118 --> 01:47:36.619
[Rocky] Careful. Collector important.

1737
01:47:36.686 --> 01:47:38.555
Yup.

1738
01:47:41.090 --> 01:47:43.159
[Mary] <i>Altitude warning.</i>

1739
01:47:43.226 --> 01:47:44.527
[Rocky] Oh. hurry. hurry.

1740
01:47:53.036 --> 01:47:55.038
[music crescendoes]

1741
01:48:00.710 --> 01:48:02.245
[Rocky] Hurry. hurry.

1742
01:48:02.946 --> 01:48:04.247
[creaks. clangs]

1743
01:48:05.748 --> 01:48:07.050
[thuds]

1744
01:48:12.632 --> 01:48:14.334
Grace?

1745
01:48:17.193 --> 01:48:18.561
Grace. status update.

1746
01:48:19.417 --> 01:48:21.119
Status update.

1747
01:48:21.718 --> 01:48:23.119
<i>Grace?</i>

1748
01:48:24.575 --> 01:48:25.843
<i>Grace is safe. question?</i>

1749
01:48:26.457 --> 01:48:28.348
[Grace] I'm okay.

1750
01:48:28.621 --> 01:48:29.543
[Rocky] Good. good. good.

1751
01:48:29.568 --> 01:48:31.570
Come inside with predator collector now.

1752
01:48:32.829 --> 01:48:34.431
[Grace] Uh.

1753
01:48:35.176 --> 01:48:37.545
[Rocky on radio]
<i>Why not moving. question?</i>

1754
01:48:39.249 --> 01:48:42.018
[Mary] <i>Warning!</i>
<i>Exterior temperature elevated.</i>

1755
01:48:42.085 --> 01:48:44.254
[Rocky] Must move now. Go. go.

1756
01:48:45.221 --> 01:48:46.723
[rattling]

1757
01:48:48.391 --> 01:48:50.193
[tense music playing]

1758
01:48:52.662 --> 01:48:54.931
No. Grace. Bad idea. Come inside.

1759
01:48:54.998 --> 01:48:56.699
I'll be there in a minute.

1760
01:48:56.766 --> 01:48:58.835
[Rocky on radio] <i>No. no. no.</i>
<i>no. no. Grace will die.</i>

1761
01:48:59.369 --> 01:49:01.170
Can repeat mission. Can try again later.

1762
01:49:01.237 --> 01:49:02.906
I don't think there is gonna be a later.

1763
01:49:03.278 --> 01:49:04.908
[Rocky] Abort. abort. abort.

1764
01:49:04.974 --> 01:49:07.911
<i>Grace will die.
No-No-No-No-No-No-No-No-No.</i>

1765
01:49:07.977 --> 01:49:09.679
[music swells]

1766
01:49:13.650 --> 01:49:14.817
[thuds]

1767
01:49:18.721 --> 01:49:20.089
[groaning]

1768
01:49:29.732 --> 01:49:31.367
[music swells]

1769
01:49:38.395 --> 01:49:40.097
- Grace?
- [Grace] I'm here!

1770
01:49:41.344 --> 01:49:42.679
Amaze. amaze. amaze!

1771
01:49:43.091 --> 01:49:44.490
- [Grace groans]
- Grace okay. question?

1772
01:49:44.514 --> 01:49:46.349
Well. I'm not dead. so yes.

1773
01:49:46.416 --> 01:49:47.850
Good. good. good. good.

1774
01:49:47.917 --> 01:49:50.086
[Grace] Where
is that noise coming from?

1775
01:49:50.333 --> 01:49:51.497
[Rocky] Noise is from all around.

1776
01:49:51.521 --> 01:49:54.223
It's loudest at port side of bedroom.

1777
01:49:54.290 --> 01:49:58.127
[Grace] The gravity's
tearing the ship apart.

1778
01:49:59.495 --> 01:50:00.997
[Rocky] We leave now. question?

1779
01:50:01.065 --> 01:50:03.633
We leave now. statement.

1780
01:50:03.700 --> 01:50:05.168
[music crescendoes]

1781
01:50:06.736 --> 01:50:08.838
[engine powering up]

1782
01:50:14.444 --> 01:50:16.379
[Mary] <i>Hull pressure warning.</i>

1783
01:50:16.446 --> 01:50:18.448
[Rocky] Hull bending
in big room below bedroom.

1784
01:50:18.473 --> 01:50:19.882
That's the fuel tanks.

1785
01:50:21.818 --> 01:50:24.153
- Oh. Bad. bad. bad.
- Well. it's not great.

1786
01:50:24.220 --> 01:50:25.540
- Bad. bad. bad.
- [Mary] <i>Warning.</i>

1787
01:50:25.588 --> 01:50:28.191
Everybody. calm down. Calm down!

1788
01:50:31.494 --> 01:50:33.063
Try and keep yourself together. Mary.

1789
01:50:33.129 --> 01:50:34.569
- Stop engine now?
- [Grace] Not yet.

1790
01:50:34.631 --> 01:50:36.432
We need to get into orbit or we'll crash!

1791
01:50:36.499 --> 01:50:39.268
I have an idea. First. no crash.

1792
01:50:39.335 --> 01:50:41.638
Then. not explode. Deal?

1793
01:50:41.861 --> 01:50:42.905
Deal!

1794
01:50:44.907 --> 01:50:46.876
Hold on.

1795
01:50:48.311 --> 01:50:49.846
[Rocky] Now?

1796
01:50:49.912 --> 01:50:51.314
Wait.

1797
01:50:54.217 --> 01:50:55.652
[Rocky] Now? Now?

1798
01:50:56.819 --> 01:50:58.655
Now!

1799
01:50:59.188 --> 01:51:01.591
[powering down]

1800
01:51:01.658 --> 01:51:02.859
[music ends]

1801
01:51:09.533 --> 01:51:10.968
Did we do it?

1802
01:51:20.543 --> 01:51:22.779
[tense music playing]

1803
01:51:32.368 --> 01:51:33.990
Why ship moving. question?

1804
01:51:34.015 --> 01:51:35.658
There's a hole in it!

1805
01:51:36.726 --> 01:51:38.461
- [alarm beeping]
- [Mary] <i>Hull breach.</i>

1806
01:51:38.528 --> 01:51:41.564
<i>Port side fuel compartments 11 and 12.</i>

1807
01:51:42.432 --> 01:51:44.034
[objects clattering]

1808
01:51:44.101 --> 01:51:46.736
Grace. What happening. question?

1809
01:51:47.470 --> 01:51:50.140
The fuel is migrating to Adrian!

1810
01:51:50.206 --> 01:51:52.675
- [hull creaking]
- [groans]

1811
01:51:55.194 --> 01:51:57.009
[Rocky] Eject bad fuel bay. question?

1812
01:51:57.034 --> 01:51:59.065
- [Grace] Yeah.
- [rapid beeping]

1813
01:51:59.132 --> 01:52:02.903
[Mary] <i>Jettison port fuel tank</i>
<i>compartment 12. Confirm.</i>

1814
01:52:03.636 --> 01:52:06.372
- [Rocky whimpering]
- [screaming]

1815
01:52:09.409 --> 01:52:11.879
- [grunts]
- [Rocky chitters]

1816
01:52:11.946 --> 01:52:14.380
- Rocky!
- [Rocky chittering]

1817
01:52:20.086 --> 01:52:21.721
[straining]

1818
01:52:24.791 --> 01:52:29.228
[Mary] <i>Jettison port fuel tank</i>
<i>compartment 11. Confirm.</i>

1819
01:52:29.532 --> 01:52:32.298
[Rocky] Eject other fuel bay.

1820
01:52:34.902 --> 01:52:36.836
[thudding]

1821
01:52:36.904 --> 01:52:38.438
[music ends]

1822
01:53:10.004 --> 01:53:11.404
[muffled chittering]

1823
01:53:11.471 --> 01:53:15.375
- [muffled blaring]
- [breathing softly]

1824
01:53:23.282 --> 01:53:25.618
[melancholy music playing]

1825
01:53:27.720 --> 01:53:28.922
[groans softly]

1826
01:53:41.001 --> 01:53:42.870
[squealing]

1827
01:53:49.342 --> 01:53:50.843
[Rocky chittering]

1828
01:53:52.779 --> 01:53:55.848
[chittering in pain]

1829
01:54:00.054 --> 01:54:02.122
[continues squealing]

1830
01:54:02.188 --> 01:54:04.824
- [tapping]
- [music swells]

1831
01:54:17.137 --> 01:54:18.671
[thudding]

1832
01:54:18.738 --> 01:54:21.108
- [hissing]
- [thuds. groans]

1833
01:54:21.175 --> 01:54:23.643
[squealing in pain]

1834
01:54:23.710 --> 01:54:25.611
[alarm blaring]

1835
01:54:29.083 --> 01:54:32.752
[flap clicks]

1836
01:54:34.154 --> 01:54:35.588
[lever clicks]

1837
01:54:35.655 --> 01:54:36.857
[beeps]

1838
01:54:39.193 --> 01:54:41.427
[dramatic music playing]

1839
01:54:51.582 --> 01:54:52.983
[Rocky chitters]

1840
01:55:01.068 --> 01:55:02.738
[Rocky continues chittering]

1841
01:55:08.788 --> 01:55:10.423
[music swells]

1842
01:55:27.673 --> 01:55:29.475
[Rocky chittering in pain]

1843
01:55:44.024 --> 01:55:46.292
[alarm beeping]

1844
01:55:46.911 --> 01:55:48.344
[Grace] One nanogram of Astrophage

1845
01:55:48.411 --> 01:55:50.581
just isn't enough to blow up a building.

1846
01:55:50.648 --> 01:55:52.212
[Dr. Lokken] The quartermaster gave him

1847
01:55:52.237 --> 01:55:54.117
one milligram by mistake.

1848
01:55:54.184 --> 01:55:55.704
That's a million times the heat energy

1849
01:55:55.786 --> 01:55:57.387
that they're prepared for.

1850
01:55:57.455 --> 01:56:00.323
A measuring mistake
killed my entire science team?

1851
01:56:00.390 --> 01:56:03.360
It doesn't matter. We have to launch.

1852
01:56:09.667 --> 01:56:12.403
If we miss the orbital window.
it'll set us back months.

1853
01:56:12.470 --> 01:56:14.070
[Grace] Yeah. but if no one's trained

1854
01:56:14.137 --> 01:56:15.740
to do the mission. it won't matter.

1855
01:56:15.806 --> 01:56:17.551
[Stratt] Casualty projections
go up exponentially

1856
01:56:17.575 --> 01:56:18.576
if we delay.

1857
01:56:18.642 --> 01:56:19.909
We launch on schedule

1858
01:56:19.976 --> 01:56:20.910
with a replacement science officer.

1859
01:56:20.977 --> 01:56:22.879
Okay. but

1860
01:56:24.448 --> 01:56:25.549
who?

1861
01:56:27.250 --> 01:56:29.986
I mean. that [sighs]

1862
01:56:45.736 --> 01:56:46.871
I'm not an astronaut.

1863
01:56:46.936 --> 01:56:48.539
I don't need an astronaut.

1864
01:56:48.606 --> 01:56:51.107
I need an expert on Astrophage
who's mission-ready.

1865
01:56:51.174 --> 01:56:52.510
I'm not ready.

1866
01:56:53.559 --> 01:56:56.414
I don't have any
training. [Chuckles softly]

1867
01:56:56.480 --> 01:56:57.748
You'll pick it up.

1868
01:56:57.815 --> 01:56:59.382
I'm not an astronaut!

1869
01:56:59.850 --> 01:57:01.752
I put the "not" in astronaut.

1870
01:57:01.819 --> 01:57:03.421
I've never done anything...

1871
01:57:03.487 --> 01:57:05.465
I've never done a space wa...
I can't even moonwalk!

1872
01:57:05.489 --> 01:57:07.425
I haven't done the whole pool thing.

1873
01:57:07.491 --> 01:57:09.627
No. no. no. This is just we do
for the picture.

1874
01:57:09.693 --> 01:57:10.795
for social media.

1875
01:57:10.861 --> 01:57:12.863
I'm not heroic in any way.

1876
01:57:12.929 --> 01:57:15.165
I get sick on an elevator.

1877
01:57:15.231 --> 01:57:17.668
Oh. perfect. There's
no elevator on the ship.

1878
01:57:17.735 --> 01:57:19.102
I cannot do this.

1879
01:57:19.169 --> 01:57:21.337
You're smart. You'll figure it out.

1880
01:57:23.823 --> 01:57:26.693
This might be very hard
for you to understand.

1881
01:57:26.760 --> 01:57:28.329
but some people are failures.

1882
01:57:28.396 --> 01:57:30.164
Some people <i>don't</i> rise to the challenge.

1883
01:57:30.231 --> 01:57:32.732
You've been present
for every major scientific

1884
01:57:32.799 --> 01:57:35.001
or strategic meeting
we've had on the mission.

1885
01:57:35.598 --> 01:57:37.281
You're missing out an
important part of the mission

1886
01:57:37.305 --> 01:57:39.173
which is the suicide part.
[chuckles nervously]

1887
01:57:39.622 --> 01:57:41.775
Grace. you'd be in very cool company.

1888
01:57:41.841 --> 01:57:43.910
If you don't go. you die anyway.

1889
01:57:43.977 --> 01:57:47.281
Yeah. but I die in 30 years with...

1890
01:57:47.348 --> 01:57:48.616
"With the rest of us."

1891
01:57:49.911 --> 01:57:53.086
You have no immediate family.
You don't even have a dog.

1892
01:57:55.848 --> 01:57:57.891
So. just so I'm clear

1893
01:57:58.526 --> 01:58:00.927
you're asking me right now

1894
01:58:03.239 --> 01:58:04.273
to give up my life.

1895
01:58:04.571 --> 01:58:06.507
I am. We all are.

1896
01:58:10.504 --> 01:58:11.738
Can I think about this?

1897
01:58:11.984 --> 01:58:13.353
You have three hours.

1898
01:58:14.975 --> 01:58:17.744
[suspenseful music playing]

1899
01:58:44.505 --> 01:58:46.806
[exhales deeply]

1900
01:58:58.352 --> 01:59:00.920
[Mary] <i>Eye movement detected.</i>

1901
01:59:01.988 --> 01:59:04.090
<i>Good morning. Dr. Grace.</i>

1902
01:59:15.135 --> 01:59:17.571
[intriguing music playing]

1903
01:59:52.673 --> 01:59:54.974
[music swells]

1904
02:00:15.596 --> 02:00:18.366
[chitters softly]

1905
02:00:22.670 --> 02:00:24.938
I'll watch you sleep. pal.

1906
02:00:29.710 --> 02:00:31.312
[Grace sighs]

1907
02:00:31.779 --> 02:00:33.314
But. uh

1908
02:00:35.067 --> 02:00:36.768
you gotta wake up.

1909
02:00:37.884 --> 02:00:40.388
[somber music playing]

1910
02:01:11.416 --> 02:01:13.154
[Grace] <i>I'm not sure what to do.</i>

1911
02:01:17.792 --> 02:01:19.760
<i>Done everything I can think of.</i>

1912
02:01:19.827 --> 02:01:21.928
[melancholy music playing]

1913
02:01:25.666 --> 02:01:27.435
<i>I made him a heat lamp.</i>

1914
02:01:50.197 --> 02:01:52.560
<i>And he left me one last message.</i>

1915
02:01:53.227 --> 02:01:55.496
[dramatic music playing]

1916
02:02:02.068 --> 02:02:03.737
[music swells]

1917
02:02:46.947 --> 02:02:49.250
[music crescendoes]

1918
02:03:34.428 --> 02:03:36.363
We have our predator.

1919
02:03:36.430 --> 02:03:39.266
Right now I'm calling it "Taumoeba."

1920
02:03:39.333 --> 02:03:41.869
And I'm sure that when you wake up.

1921
02:03:41.936 --> 02:03:45.639
you'll have a lot to say
about why that's a bad name

1922
02:03:45.884 --> 02:03:48.275
because it's just
an amoeba from Tau Ceti.

1923
02:03:48.342 --> 02:03:50.377
and we're putting "Tau"
in front of "amoeba."

1924
02:03:50.444 --> 02:03:53.514
But I would argue there's
an elegance to that.

1925
02:03:53.581 --> 02:03:54.515
A simplicity.

1926
02:03:54.582 --> 02:03:56.350
Let's not fight about it now.

1927
02:03:56.658 --> 02:03:58.919
We'll table it and we'll...

1928
02:03:58.986 --> 02:04:01.388
I did a test at different
atmospheric variables

1929
02:04:01.455 --> 02:04:04.758
and. fun fact. every time
I introduced nitrogen

1930
02:04:04.825 --> 02:04:06.327
[blows raspberry] it died.

1931
02:04:06.393 --> 02:04:07.861
And I know what you're thinking.

1932
02:04:07.928 --> 02:04:09.830
"Well. that's terrible
because that's a problem

1933
02:04:09.897 --> 02:04:12.866
'cause we need it to survive
in the conditions of Venus."

1934
02:04:12.933 --> 02:04:14.613
Obviously. I had to figure out
how to breed

1935
02:04:14.668 --> 02:04:17.571
a new strain of
nitrogen-resistant Taumoeba.

1936
02:04:18.806 --> 02:04:20.407
And guess what I used?

1937
02:04:20.474 --> 02:04:24.378
The breeder tanks that we made
with your xenonite.

1938
02:04:25.245 --> 02:04:26.847
And you know what?

1939
02:04:26.914 --> 02:04:27.914
[kisses]

1940
02:04:27.954 --> 02:04:30.142
Now we're just
a couple of very cool dudes

1941
02:04:30.367 --> 02:04:34.071
with their very own strain of
nitrogen-resistant Taumoeba.

1942
02:04:34.455 --> 02:04:35.615
Really. all we have to do now

1943
02:04:35.673 --> 02:04:38.242
is breed enough to survive the trip.

1944
02:04:38.309 --> 02:04:40.311
And you gotta wake up

1945
02:04:40.377 --> 02:04:41.846
because I don't know how to get

1946
02:04:41.912 --> 02:04:44.048
your half of the Taumoeba to Erid.

1947
02:04:45.015 --> 02:04:46.484
So.

1948
02:04:46.917 --> 02:04:49.253
No pressure

1949
02:04:49.278 --> 02:04:52.014
but we did make a deal.

1950
02:05:00.464 --> 02:05:03.534
[dramatic music continues]

1951
02:05:59.590 --> 02:06:01.692
[thudding]

1952
02:06:12.169 --> 02:06:13.671
[Grace] Shh.

1953
02:06:13.737 --> 02:06:15.339
Grace?

1954
02:06:20.678 --> 02:06:22.713
Rock. could you just

1955
02:06:22.780 --> 02:06:27.151
give me a little chance please
to sleep a little?

1956
02:06:28.786 --> 02:06:30.821
[chitters]

1957
02:06:31.956 --> 02:06:33.791
[music swells]

1958
02:06:42.414 --> 02:06:44.916
[Rocky] Did we find predator?

1959
02:06:53.673 --> 02:06:56.209
No? Is yes.

1960
02:06:58.016 --> 02:07:00.584
[upbeat triumphant music playing]

1961
02:07:12.123 --> 02:07:14.492
Amaze. amaze. amaze.

1962
02:07:14.517 --> 02:07:16.720
Rocky breeder tank design.

1963
02:07:17.546 --> 02:07:18.469
Good job. Rock.

1964
02:07:18.535 --> 02:07:21.372
[Rocky] We can go home. statement.

1965
02:07:22.940 --> 02:07:24.675
We can go home.

1966
02:07:25.242 --> 02:07:27.112
[Rocky] Fist my bump.

1967
02:07:27.177 --> 02:07:28.979
Nope.

1968
02:07:29.047 --> 02:07:30.414
It's still not right.

1969
02:07:30.814 --> 02:07:33.484
- I'll do it.
- [Rocky] Good. good. good.

1970
02:07:34.002 --> 02:07:37.172
So what we do now. question?

1971
02:07:41.059 --> 02:07:42.292
We party.

1972
02:07:42.359 --> 02:07:44.361
[music swells]

1973
02:07:54.738 --> 02:07:55.973
Wow.

1974
02:07:56.473 --> 02:07:58.942
[Rocky] Is special clothing
for celebration.

1975
02:07:59.010 --> 02:08:03.180
[Grace] You're making me think
that I have to. uh. up my game.

1976
02:08:03.247 --> 02:08:05.100
- What is this?
- [Grace] If you don't mind.

1977
02:08:05.125 --> 02:08:07.161
- Rocky get one!
- [Grace] There you go.

1978
02:08:07.584 --> 02:08:10.254
- [Rocky] Is good.
- Yeah.

1979
02:08:12.823 --> 02:08:15.026
It's not much. Just a little something.

1980
02:08:15.436 --> 02:08:16.727
Your very own laptop.

1981
02:08:16.794 --> 02:08:18.529
My portable Earth thinking-machine!

1982
02:08:18.827 --> 02:08:20.326
[Grace] With all human knowledge.

1983
02:08:20.351 --> 02:08:21.419
Thank. thank. thank.

1984
02:08:21.444 --> 02:08:22.610
And just one more thing.

1985
02:08:23.300 --> 02:08:25.235
[Rocky] Yes?

1986
02:08:26.171 --> 02:08:27.738
What this?

1987
02:08:27.805 --> 02:08:29.273
It's Earth.

1988
02:08:30.908 --> 02:08:33.377
So you can remember me.

1989
02:08:41.497 --> 02:08:44.333
[Rocky] Rocky can't forget.

1990
02:08:48.059 --> 02:08:49.927
I didn't get you anything.

1991
02:08:51.328 --> 02:08:53.263
You gave me everything.

1992
02:08:54.722 --> 02:08:56.790
[Rocky] But if I were to
give you something?

1993
02:09:00.270 --> 02:09:02.372
It'd be pretty cool to see your ship.

1994
02:09:02.439 --> 02:09:04.308
[Rocky chitters]

1995
02:09:04.374 --> 02:09:06.243
[upbeat music playing]

1996
02:09:10.115 --> 02:09:12.449
[Rocky chittering]

1997
02:09:28.966 --> 02:09:31.002
[music swells]

1998
02:10:20.918 --> 02:10:22.148
[Grace] <i>I understand that you think</i>

1999
02:10:22.172 --> 02:10:24.207
I'm the right person for this mission.

2000
02:10:26.042 --> 02:10:27.642
But.

2001
02:10:31.772 --> 02:10:33.406
I can't do it.

2002
02:10:37.701 --> 02:10:39.168
[smacks lips]

2003
02:10:40.849 --> 02:10:42.316
I can't do it.

2004
02:10:43.669 --> 02:10:45.369
[Grace inhales deeply]

2005
02:10:48.208 --> 02:10:50.514
You'll find a solution. [Chuckles]

2006
02:10:50.581 --> 02:10:52.749
You are my solution.

2007
02:10:57.513 --> 02:10:59.403
My place is in the classroom. [Sighs]

2008
02:10:59.428 --> 02:11:00.930
Stop pretending
this is about your students.

2009
02:11:00.954 --> 02:11:02.423
It's so insulting.

2010
02:11:04.111 --> 02:11:05.814
Grace. we will lose

2011
02:11:06.614 --> 02:11:09.684
a quarter of the world's population

2012
02:11:09.751 --> 02:11:11.352
in the next 30 years.

2013
02:11:12.586 --> 02:11:14.856
And that assumes
that the nations of the world

2014
02:11:14.923 --> 02:11:17.291
work together to ration food.

2015
02:11:18.292 --> 02:11:19.728
Which they won't.

2016
02:11:21.462 --> 02:11:23.130
So I'd double the estimate.

2017
02:11:23.197 --> 02:11:24.876
And if you would
truly care about the children.

2018
02:11:24.900 --> 02:11:26.333
or anyone else for that matter.

2019
02:11:26.400 --> 02:11:28.402
you'd get on that ship.

2020
02:11:31.272 --> 02:11:32.974
[clears throat]

2021
02:11:33.040 --> 02:11:35.209
I understand the stakes.

2022
02:11:36.644 --> 02:11:37.746
I do.

2023
02:11:41.816 --> 02:11:43.551
But I don't have it in me.

2024
02:11:49.692 --> 02:11:51.492
[sniffles] My mind is made up.

2025
02:11:53.294 --> 02:11:55.129
[groans softly. sniffles]

2026
02:11:55.195 --> 02:11:56.831
I'm sorry. but. uh.

2027
02:11:59.099 --> 02:12:01.535
But you just can't talk me into it.

2028
02:12:02.202 --> 02:12:04.005
[whispering] I'm sorry.

2029
02:12:05.075 --> 02:12:08.246
I'm not trying to talk you into anything.

2030
02:12:09.476 --> 02:12:11.345
I am

2031
02:12:12.079 --> 02:12:15.149
trying to make you understand

2032
02:12:15.669 --> 02:12:17.336
what I'm about to do next.

2033
02:12:18.085 --> 02:12:19.721
Yeah? Please.

2034
02:12:19.788 --> 02:12:22.122
Stay calm. Come in.

2035
02:12:25.760 --> 02:12:27.094
What is this?

2036
02:12:27.161 --> 02:12:28.697
Mission plan will state that

2037
02:12:28.763 --> 02:12:30.749
we induced your coma early
to maximize your safety.

2038
02:12:30.773 --> 02:12:32.309
You will be remembered as a hero.

2039
02:12:33.702 --> 02:12:35.302
Come on. This is crazy.

2040
02:12:35.369 --> 02:12:37.204
- I have to do it.
- [sniffles] You're not.

2041
02:12:37.271 --> 02:12:39.340
Come on. What are you doing?

2042
02:12:39.406 --> 02:12:42.242
This may seem like me betraying you.

2043
02:12:42.309 --> 02:12:44.012
but it's actually me believing in you.

2044
02:12:44.079 --> 02:12:46.014
Sure feels like you're betraying me.

2045
02:12:46.413 --> 02:12:47.489
Don't make this harder. please.

2046
02:12:47.513 --> 02:12:49.147
[Grace] Come on. guys.

2047
02:12:52.152 --> 02:12:54.089
Let's keep talking about it.

2048
02:12:54.154 --> 02:12:55.522
[objects clattering]

2049
02:12:56.891 --> 02:12:58.891
[voice breaking] Sit down
and we do it differently.

2050
02:12:59.593 --> 02:13:00.829
[Grace screams]

2051
02:13:00.895 --> 02:13:03.230
[tense music playing]

2052
02:13:07.102 --> 02:13:08.670
[Stratt] Yeah. he's running.

2053
02:13:16.143 --> 02:13:18.445
- [panting]
- [music swells]

2054
02:13:21.116 --> 02:13:22.984
[both groaning]

2055
02:13:23.374 --> 02:13:24.919
No.

2056
02:13:25.186 --> 02:13:26.988
No. No.

2057
02:13:27.983 --> 02:13:30.959
Carl. I can't do it.

2058
02:13:31.026 --> 02:13:32.359
No!

2059
02:13:32.426 --> 02:13:35.562
Don't do it! Don't do it! Don't do it.

2060
02:13:37.032 --> 02:13:38.265
You know who you are.

2061
02:13:38.332 --> 02:13:39.801
[groans. pants]

2062
02:13:40.068 --> 02:13:41.069
[Grace] Carl!

2063
02:13:41.135 --> 02:13:42.836
You're gonna do great.

2064
02:13:43.604 --> 02:13:46.040
[Grace wheezing]

2065
02:13:46.107 --> 02:13:48.408
[pensive music playing]

2066
02:14:14.735 --> 02:14:17.906
I'm trying to think
if there's anything I forgot.

2067
02:14:20.421 --> 02:14:22.069
Fuel tank fix okay. question?

2068
02:14:22.109 --> 02:14:23.554
Oh. yeah. yeah. They're working great.

2069
02:14:23.578 --> 02:14:26.280
[Rocky] Oh. good. Happy. happy. happy.

2070
02:14:26.648 --> 02:14:28.282
[chuckles softly]

2071
02:14:30.742 --> 02:14:32.245
[Grace] Well.

2072
02:14:33.789 --> 02:14:35.022
My friend.

2073
02:14:35.089 --> 02:14:37.392
Yes. friend?

2074
02:14:38.619 --> 02:14:42.322
I'm not sure what to say. so just gonna.

2075
02:14:50.618 --> 02:14:51.752
Grace?

2076
02:14:55.129 --> 02:14:57.198
No one to watch you sleep.

2077
02:14:58.263 --> 02:14:59.799
Yeah.

2078
02:15:00.948 --> 02:15:04.486
[Rocky] You are very brave.

2079
02:15:06.702 --> 02:15:09.023
Oh. I don't know about that.

2080
02:15:10.859 --> 02:15:14.796
[Rocky] You are bravest human
I have ever met.

2081
02:15:14.863 --> 02:15:16.398
[chuckles softly]

2082
02:15:16.465 --> 02:15:17.632
Hey.

2083
02:15:17.699 --> 02:15:19.868
- Is joke.
- I know.

2084
02:15:19.935 --> 02:15:23.003
I only meet one human. and is you!

2085
02:15:23.070 --> 02:15:24.238
I get it.

2086
02:15:24.305 --> 02:15:25.640
It's a good joke.

2087
02:15:25.707 --> 02:15:26.875
[Rocky] Good joke.

2088
02:15:27.861 --> 02:15:29.276
All right. Well

2089
02:15:29.343 --> 02:15:31.713
[solemn music playing]

2090
02:15:35.004 --> 02:15:36.304
Goodbye.

2091
02:15:37.181 --> 02:15:39.053
[Rocky] No understand word.

2092
02:15:39.416 --> 02:15:42.223
Means. uh. see you later.

2093
02:15:42.289 --> 02:15:44.291
[Rocky] But I won't see you later.

2094
02:15:48.830 --> 02:15:50.365
I know.

2095
02:15:52.567 --> 02:15:54.703
How do you say goodbye back home?

2096
02:15:54.769 --> 02:15:55.937
[Rocky] We don't.

2097
02:15:56.003 --> 02:15:57.539
[Grace] Hmm.

2098
02:15:57.606 --> 02:15:58.807
[Rocky] We do this.

2099
02:15:58.874 --> 02:16:00.609
[chittering]

2100
02:16:04.713 --> 02:16:07.248
[enthralling music swells]

2101
02:16:52.761 --> 02:16:54.061
[music ends]

2102
02:16:54.930 --> 02:16:57.566
[pensive music playing]

2103
02:17:51.293 --> 02:17:52.786
[Mary] <i>Journey to Earth</i>

2104
02:17:53.270 --> 02:17:57.525
<i>will take 4 years. 2 months and 11 days.</i>

2105
02:18:01.429 --> 02:18:03.498
[music fades slowly]

2106
02:18:07.035 --> 02:18:08.737
[Latin folk song playing]

2107
02:18:12.574 --> 02:18:14.709
[students chanting] <i>Lava! Lava!</i>

2108
02:18:14.776 --> 02:18:16.243
Lava!

2109
02:18:48.743 --> 02:18:49.778
[breathes deeply]

2110
02:18:49.844 --> 02:18:52.047
[alarm blaring]

2111
02:18:52.113 --> 02:18:54.549
[Mary] <i>Contaminant detected.</i>

2112
02:18:56.016 --> 02:18:58.652
<i>Contaminant detected.</i>

2113
02:19:00.395 --> 02:19:02.189
<i>Contaminant detected.</i>

2114
02:19:02.512 --> 02:19:07.529
<i>Contaminant detected.</i>

2115
02:19:08.163 --> 02:19:10.398
<i>Contaminant detected.</i>

2116
02:19:11.166 --> 02:19:13.535
<i>Contaminant detected.</i>

2117
02:19:22.410 --> 02:19:24.278
[hissing]

2118
02:19:27.115 --> 02:19:29.283
[tense music playing]

2119
02:19:54.542 --> 02:19:55.977
[Grace] <i>There's a leak.</i>

2120
02:19:57.545 --> 02:19:59.848
<i>The problem is the xenonite.</i>

2121
02:19:59.914 --> 02:20:02.016
<i>The Taumoeba can get through it.</i>

2122
02:20:02.717 --> 02:20:05.176
<i>Probably 'cause we bred it
in the xenonite breeder tanks.</i>

2123
02:20:05.201 --> 02:20:06.903
<i>it evolved to escape it.</i>

2124
02:20:07.789 --> 02:20:08.848
<i>I was able to stop it</i>

2125
02:20:08.873 --> 02:20:11.576
<i>before it ate all the
Astrophage on the ship.</i>

2126
02:20:13.376 --> 02:20:15.612
Rocky's ship is built of xenonite.

2127
02:20:16.838 --> 02:20:19.941
The Taumoeba will already
be in his fuel lines.

2128
02:20:19.966 --> 02:20:21.568
And he won't be able to find the leak

2129
02:20:21.593 --> 02:20:23.661
because the leak is the ship itself.

2130
02:20:24.038 --> 02:20:27.742
He'll be without any fuel. Stranded.

2131
02:20:27.809 --> 02:20:30.878
His life support systems will fail.

2132
02:20:32.579 --> 02:20:36.050
And if that doesn't kill him.
the radiation sickness will.

2133
02:20:38.581 --> 02:20:40.316
He's looking at a long

2134
02:20:40.821 --> 02:20:42.190
slow

2135
02:20:44.415 --> 02:20:45.950
painful death

2136
02:20:47.800 --> 02:20:49.201
alone.

2137
02:21:12.938 --> 02:21:14.573
<i>I can't do both.</i>

2138
02:21:16.152 --> 02:21:18.154
<i>I can go home</i>

2139
02:21:21.146 --> 02:21:22.747
<i>or I can save Rocky.</i>

2140
02:21:41.984 --> 02:21:44.820
<i>I've sent you detailed logs
of all of our findings.</i>

2141
02:21:44.887 --> 02:21:46.788
<i>And enough Taumoeba for you</i>

2142
02:21:46.855 --> 02:21:52.261
<i>to start your very own Taumoeba farm.</i>

2143
02:21:52.955 --> 02:21:54.496
<i>At least I never have to hear you say.</i>

2144
02:21:54.563 --> 02:21:56.131
<i>"I told you so."</i>

2145
02:21:57.505 --> 02:21:59.307
Even though you were right.

2146
02:22:00.235 --> 02:22:02.537
[folk rock song playing]

2147
02:24:01.323 --> 02:24:03.124
[song ends]

2148
02:24:12.834 --> 02:24:15.270
[intriguing music playing]

2149
02:24:24.946 --> 02:24:26.514
[inaudible] Rocky!

2150
02:24:32.088 --> 02:24:33.755
[inaudible] Hey!

2151
02:24:36.547 --> 02:24:39.117
[thuds reverberate]

2152
02:24:40.895 --> 02:24:43.331
[inaudible] Come on. Rock!

2153
02:24:45.367 --> 02:24:48.269
[thuds reverberate]

2154
02:25:05.854 --> 02:25:07.689
[pleasant music playing]

2155
02:25:22.038 --> 02:25:24.339
[music swells]

2156
02:25:32.048 --> 02:25:33.782
[Rocky chittering]

2157
02:25:38.253 --> 02:25:40.789
[chittering]

2158
02:25:41.611 --> 02:25:43.312
I'm here. buddy.

2159
02:25:43.458 --> 02:25:45.760
[music crescendoes]

2160
02:26:06.115 --> 02:26:07.983
[Grace] <i>Earth. Rocky.</i>

2161
02:26:08.050 --> 02:26:09.584
<i>Rocky. Earth.</i>

2162
02:26:09.651 --> 02:26:12.353
<i>Hello. Earth. I am Rocky.</i>

2163
02:26:12.420 --> 02:26:14.023
<i>I am Rocky from Erid.</i>

2164
02:26:14.090 --> 02:26:16.758
<i>I am not Rocky from movie.
No. no. no. no.</i>

2165
02:26:16.825 --> 02:26:18.793
[Grace] <i>I'm pretty sure they know that.</i>

2166
02:26:18.860 --> 02:26:21.329
<i>I've left you detailed logs
of all of our findings</i>

2167
02:26:21.396 --> 02:26:25.333
<i>and I threw in a little
something else just for fun.</i>

2168
02:26:27.268 --> 02:26:29.904
<i>Hopefully it all makes sense.</i>

2169
02:26:29.972 --> 02:26:31.207
<i>And if not.</i>

2170
02:26:31.272 --> 02:26:32.907
<i>You're smart.</i>

2171
02:26:33.475 --> 02:26:34.943
<i>You'll figure it out.</i>

2172
02:26:36.544 --> 02:26:38.717
<i>This is Dr. Captain Ryland Grace</i>

2173
02:26:38.742 --> 02:26:40.175
<i>reporting from the</i> Hail Mary.

2174
02:26:40.615 --> 02:26:42.817
<i>As the Eridians say</i>

2175
02:26:45.187 --> 02:26:47.722
[upbeat rock music playing]

2176
02:26:59.258 --> 02:27:00.626
Let's begin.

2177
02:27:32.801 --> 02:27:34.236
[music ends]

2178
02:27:34.302 --> 02:27:37.338
[alarm ringing]

2179
02:27:38.439 --> 02:27:40.742
[classic rock song playing]

2180
02:27:48.284 --> 02:27:50.785
[toothbrush buzzing]

2181
02:27:53.189 --> 02:27:54.422
Good morning. Armando.

2182
02:27:54.489 --> 02:27:55.958
[whirring]

2183
02:27:56.025 --> 02:27:57.725
You shouldn't have.

2184
02:27:57.792 --> 02:27:59.360
[knock on door]

2185
02:28:00.129 --> 02:28:01.930
[knocking intensifies]

2186
02:28:02.530 --> 02:28:03.966
That's a noogie.

2187
02:28:04.033 --> 02:28:05.500
I'm coming!

2188
02:28:05.567 --> 02:28:07.702
[knocking rapidly]

2189
02:28:08.670 --> 02:28:10.338
[waves splashing]

2190
02:28:12.785 --> 02:28:14.263
(Why so long?)

2191
02:28:14.642 --> 02:28:15.630
Why you always gotta be so early?

2192
02:28:15.655 --> 02:28:17.620
(I knocked and knocked on door.)

2193
02:28:17.645 --> 02:28:20.372
Yeah. I know. and I ignored you.

2194
02:28:20.397 --> 02:28:21.198
(Grace. the door.)

2195
02:28:21.419 --> 02:28:24.253
Yeah. Okay.

2196
02:28:24.686 --> 02:28:27.355
Why? I thought
this was a safe neighborhood.

2197
02:28:27.379 --> 02:28:28.532
(I made door. You slammed door.)

2198
02:28:28.556 --> 02:28:31.626
Okay. It's just.
Armando likes the fresh air.

2199
02:28:32.660 --> 02:28:34.729
[upbeat music playing]

2200
02:28:42.437 --> 02:28:44.039
[rumbling]

2201
02:28:45.207 --> 02:28:47.176
Can we talk about the water
temperature a little bit?

2202
02:28:47.200 --> 02:28:48.278
(Yes.)

2203
02:28:48.303 --> 02:28:49.395
It's amazing.

2204
02:28:49.420 --> 02:28:51.121
Just that you've done it at all.

2205
02:28:52.380 --> 02:28:53.816
Very cold.

2206
02:28:54.516 --> 02:28:56.484
And. before. it was boiling.

2207
02:28:56.551 --> 02:28:58.520
Is there an in between?

2208
02:28:58.544 --> 02:29:00.544
(I tell Adriana to get straight.)

2209
02:29:06.628 --> 02:29:09.431
Please tell
the bio dome illumination team

2210
02:29:09.497 --> 02:29:11.700
that it's perfect now.

2211
02:29:11.970 --> 02:29:14.351
(You want more sun?)

2212
02:29:14.402 --> 02:29:15.975
Oh. no. this is...

2213
02:29:16.000 --> 02:29:18.604
You know I'm a sucker for the fog.

2214
02:29:27.225 --> 02:29:28.346
(Grace.)

2215
02:29:28.854 --> 02:29:29.975
Yeah. pal.

2216
02:29:30.624 --> 02:29:33.389
(Eridian scientists are ready...)

2217
02:29:33.413 --> 02:29:35.710
(...equip Hail Mary. For trip home.)

2218
02:29:43.873 --> 02:29:46.107
Can I think about it?

2219
02:29:46.131 --> 02:29:48.748
(Yes. you can think long time.)

2220
02:30:23.471 --> 02:30:25.775
[upbeat music continues]

2221
02:30:35.948 --> 02:30:39.118
Good morning. class.

2222
02:30:39.521 --> 02:30:43.324
Okay. Everyone take their seats.

2223
02:30:43.787 --> 02:30:45.421
Let's wake up.

2224
02:30:49.231 --> 02:30:50.900
Who can tell me the speed of light?

2225
02:30:50.966 --> 02:30:52.968
[students chittering]

2226
02:30:57.873 --> 02:30:59.141
[music ends]

2227
02:30:59.208 --> 02:31:01.543
  [gospel song playing]

2228
02:32:55.324 --> 02:32:56.926
[song fades]

2229
02:32:57.625 --> 02:32:59.962
[ethereal chorus vocalizing]

2230
02:36:24.699 --> 02:36:26.701
[music fades slowly]

